window.I18N_ZH={"AI":"AI","personal project":"个人项目","Hermes — building an LLM-in-the-loop":"Hermes——搭一个 LLM-in-the-loop 的","trading research system":"交易研究系统","A US-stock research system I built for myself — the LLM is on a tight leash: it narrates the numbers, it never computes them.":"一个我做给自己用的美股研究系统——LLM 被拴得很紧:它只负责把数字讲成话,从不负责算这些数字。","A personal side project, not investment advice. There is no auto-trading anywhere in it — the system only recommends prices; I place every order by hand. What follows is the honest problem-and-solution log of building it: the messy parts, the guardrails, and where I know the gaps still are.":"一个个人副业项目,不构成投资建议。整套东西里没有任何自动交易——系统只推荐价格,每一笔订单都是我手动下的。下面是搭它过程中如实记下的问题与解法:狼狈的地方、护栏,以及我清楚知道的那些缺口还在哪。","3 repos · one pipeline":"3 个 repo · 一条 pipeline","news → signals → validation":"新闻 → 信号 → 验证","≤2 LLM calls per run":"每次运行 ≤2 次 LLM 调用","model narrates, code computes":"模型讲话,代码算数","recommend-only · every order by hand":"只推荐 · 每笔订单手动下","what it is":"它是什么","Three repos, one":"三个 repo,一条","pipeline":"pipeline","The system is deliberately three separate repos that form a pipeline:":"整套系统刻意拆成三个独立的 repo,合起来是一条 pipeline:","news → signals → offline validation":"新闻 → 信号 → 离线验证",". They are split by lifecycle and data source, not for tidiness — the reasons are in Q1.":"。拆分是按生命周期和数据源来的,不是为了整洁——理由在 Q1。","hermes-news — the daily aggregator":"hermes-news——每日聚合器","Pulls 20+ RSS/HTML sources (WSJ, MarketWatch, FT, BBC, HuggingFace papers, Arxiv, plus MY sources), an LLM extracts the takeaways and levels, then it renders static HTML plus one JSON per day and pushes a summary to a chat channel. Four buckets: US stocks, MY stocks, AI, macro. Deploys to Vercel.":"拉取 20+ 个 RSS/HTML 源(WSJ、MarketWatch、FT、BBC、HuggingFace papers、Arxiv,外加马来西亚的源),由 LLM 提炼要点和点位,然后渲染静态 HTML 加每天一份 JSON,把摘要推到一个 chat 频道。分四个桶:美股、马股、AI、宏观。部署在 Vercel。","hermes-trading — the live assistant":"hermes-trading——实时助手","Three independent strategy pipelines behind one FastAPI dashboard:":"一个 FastAPI dashboard 后面挂着三条独立的策略 pipeline:","A 长投":"A 长投","(value, weekly — ROE/ROIC, Altman Z, Piotroski F, Graham fair value),":"(价值,周频——ROE/ROIC、Altman Z、Piotroski F、Graham 合理价),","B 做T":"B 做T","(swing, daily — ATR stops, pivots, Bollinger/Donchian, risk-based sizing),":"(波段,日频——ATR 止损、pivot、Bollinger/Donchian、按风险定仓),","C 大佬":"C 大佬","(institutional flow, daily — 13F diffs, Form 4 insider clusters, ARK). Data from Finnhub + yfinance; config hot-reloads from a web drawer; a bot answers":"(机构动向,日频——13F 变动、Form 4 内部人集群、ARK)。数据来自 Finnhub + yfinance;配置从一个网页抽屉里热加载;一个 bot 按需回应","on demand.":"。","hermes-backtest — offline validation":"hermes-backtest——离线验证","Where a strategy earns the right to exist before anything goes live. A \"Stage 0 honest engine\" proves costs and slippage are actually deducted, then Stage 1 baseline rules, plus a pile of intraday backtests and a \"review agent\" that writes a challenge report. Data from Moomoo OpenD (local daemon) + yfinance; results gitignored.":"策略在上线之前,先在这里挣得存在的资格。一个「Stage 0 诚实引擎」证明成本和滑点真的被扣掉了,然后是 Stage 1 基线规则,外加一堆日内回测和一个会写「挑战报告」的 review agent。数据来自 Moomoo OpenD(本地 daemon)+ yfinance;结果 gitignore 掉。","How they connect: backtest is where a strategy earns the right to exist — offline, cost-aware; trading runs the survivors live and only":"它们怎么连起来:backtest 是策略挣得存在资格的地方——离线、算成本;trading 把活下来的拿去实盘跑,而且只","recommends":"推荐","; news feeds context and headlines into the value pipeline's narrative.":";news 把背景和头条喂进价值 pipeline 的叙事里。","the llm approach":"LLM 怎么用","The LLM is":"LLM 是","swappable":"可替换的",", and tiny":",而且用得很省","The model choice is deliberately swappable, and it evolved. The rule that matters most: the model only writes words — every number it sees was already computed by deterministic code.":"模型的选择是刻意做成可替换的,而且一路在变。最要紧的一条规则:模型只写字——它看到的每一个数字,都是确定性代码先算好的。","Started on DeepSeek v4":"起步用的是 DeepSeek v4","(via OpenRouter),":"(走 OpenRouter),",", for the news extraction.":",用于新闻提炼。","Now runs Xiaomi MiMo 2.5":"现在跑的是小米 MiMo 2.5","for the trading assistant — an Anthropic-compatible endpoint (":"用于交易助手——一个 Anthropic 兼容的 endpoint(","message API) at":"message API),temperature 设为","OpenRouter stays wired in as the swap layer.":"OpenRouter 一直接在那儿当替换层。","Model and base URL are env-driven (":"模型和 base URL 都由环境变量驱动(","), so I can A/B a different model without touching pipeline code.":"),所以我换一个模型做 A/B,不用动 pipeline 代码。","LLM use is deliberately tiny:":"LLM 的用量刻意压得很小:","a hard cap of ≤2 LLM calls per pipeline run, batched. All math and screening is deterministic code; the model only writes narrative and classifies cause. Pipeline B, the website, and every JSON/chat formatter make zero LLM calls.":"硬性上限——每次 pipeline 运行 ≤2 次 LLM 调用,还是批量的。所有算数和筛选都是确定性代码;模型只写叙事、只做归因分类。Pipeline B、网站,以及每一个 JSON/chat 格式化器,LLM 调用次数都是零。","problems & solutions":"问题与解法","Problems &":"问题与","solutions":"解法","Each one is the same shape: the problem, what I tried, how I solved it. A few carry short illustrative snippets — rewritten to show the idea, not lifted from source.":"每一条都是同一个形状:问题、试过什么、怎么解的。有几条带了短的示意代码——是为讲清思路重写的,不是从源码里抄的。","Why three repos instead of one Hermes monorepo?":"为什么是三个 repo,而不是一个 Hermes monorepo?","The problem:":"问题:","the three concerns have completely different lifecycles. Backtesting is throwaway research — dozens of one-off scripts I run once and never touch again. The live assistant has to stay clean and always-on. The news thing is basically a static-site generator.":"这三件事的生命周期完全不同。回测是用完就扔的研究——几十个一次性脚本,跑一遍就再也不碰。实时助手得保持干净、常驻在线。新闻那块基本就是个静态站点生成器。","What I tried:":"试过什么:","early on it was one workspace. Mixing 40 experimental backtest scripts next to the always-on trading server made the trading repo look terrifying and made it hard to reason about \"what's production.\"":"最早是一个 workspace。40 个实验性回测脚本跟常驻的交易服务堆在一起,让 trading repo 看着吓人,也很难分清「哪些是生产的」。","How I solved it:":"怎么解的:","split by lifecycle and by data source. Backtest is a research sandbox with results gitignored; trading is the disciplined production repo with one FastAPI process and a strict build contract; news is a self-contained generator that deploys to Vercel. Each has its own README, its own skill file, and its own changelog GitHub Action.":"按生命周期和数据源拆开。backtest 是个研究沙盒,结果 gitignore 掉;trading 是有纪律的生产 repo,一个 FastAPI 进程加一份严格的 build 约定;news 是个自包含的生成器,部署到 Vercel。每个都有自己的 README、自己的 skill 文件、自己的 changelog GitHub Action。","LLMs return \"JSON\" that isn't valid JSON. How do you parse it reliably?":"LLM 返回的「JSON」不是合法 JSON。怎么可靠地解析?","the model wraps output in code fences, adds prose before the array, puts raw newlines inside string values, and — worst — gets truncated at max_tokens mid-object.":"模型会把输出包在代码围栏里,在数组前面加一段散文,在字符串值里塞进裸换行,而且——最糟的——在 max_tokens 处把对象截断到一半。","fails on all of these and the whole day's render dies.":"对这些全都会失败,整天的渲染直接挂掉。","plain":"先是直接",", then a regex to strip code fences. Regex alone still died on truncation and embedded newlines.":",然后加一段正则去剥代码围栏。光靠正则,碰到截断和内嵌换行还是会挂。","a hand-written extractor that repairs instead of just parsing — strip fences, seek to the first bracket, escape stray newlines that appear inside strings, then walk the brace depth and auto-close any unclosed brackets when the response was cut off, before finally validating. If it still won't parse, return nothing and skip rather than crash.":"一个手写的提取器——不是光解析,而是修复:剥掉围栏,定位到第一个括号,把字符串内部的游离换行转义掉,然后按括号深度走一遍,在响应被截断时自动补齐没闭合的括号,最后才去校验。要是还解析不了,就返回空、跳过,而不是崩掉。","The trading LLM sometimes returns no text at all. Why, and how do you handle it?":"交易用的 LLM 有时压根不返回文本。为什么,又怎么处理?","an Anthropic-compatible model can return a thinking/reasoning block first, so naively grabbing the first content block gives you the reasoning, not the answer — or an empty string.":"Anthropic 兼容的模型可能先返回一个 thinking/reasoning 块,所以傻乎乎地取第一个 content 块,拿到的是推理过程,不是答案——或者干脆是空串。","reading the first content block. Wrong block type gives garbage or nothing.":"读第一个 content 块。块类型不对,拿到的要么是垃圾,要么什么都没有。","iterate the content blocks and return the first one whose type is":"遍历所有 content 块,返回第一个类型是","; log the block types seen when there's no text block, so I can debug it. And every caller degrades gracefully — if the call returns nothing, the pipeline falls back to a raw, non-LLM summary instead of failing the run.":"的那个;没有 text 块时,把见到的块类型记进日志,方便我排查。而且每个调用方都会优雅降级——调用返回空时,pipeline 退回到一份不带 LLM 的原始摘要,而不是让整次运行失败。","How do you stop an LLM from inventing prices and numbers in the commentary?":"怎么防止 LLM 在点评里编价格、编数字?","if you let a model write \"market narrative,\" it will confidently state a price or a % move that never happened. In a trading context that's dangerous.":"你要是让模型去写「市场叙事」,它会一脸笃定地报一个从没发生过的价格或涨跌幅。在交易语境里,这很危险。","nothing structural at first — just trusting the prose.":"一开始什么结构性手段都没有——纯靠信任那段文字。","the structural rule is that the LLM":"结构性的规则是:LLM","only narrates pre-computed numbers, never computes them":"只把预先算好的数字讲成话,从不自己去算",". All screening, levels and scores are deterministic code; the model receives the finished numbers as input at low temperature and is instructed to cite only supplied data. The sentiment score, for example, is computed in code (SPY return + VIX + % above the 200-day average) — the model only writes the words around it.":"。所有筛选、点位、评分都是确定性代码;模型在低 temperature 下拿到算完的数字作为输入,并被要求只引用喂给它的数据。比如情绪分,是代码算的(SPY 涨跌 + VIX + 站上 200 日均线的比例)——模型只负责写它周围那些字。","Honest limitation:":"如实说的局限:","today this is a prompt-plus-low-temperature guardrail, not an automated verifier. I don't yet cross-check every number the model echoes against the input programmatically — that post-hoc echo-verification is a known gap I'd close next. It's tolerable for now because the model is handed finished numbers and asked only to narrate, so the blast radius of a slip is prose, not a traded level.":"今天这套还只是「prompt + 低 temperature」的护栏,不是自动校验器。我还没做到用程序把模型复述的每个数字都跟输入交叉核对一遍——这种事后的复述核验是个已知缺口,是我下一步要补的。现在还能忍,是因为模型拿到的是算好的数字、只被要求转述,所以出岔子的波及范围是文字,不是一个真去交易的点位。","Yahoo Finance rate-limits bulk downloads. How did you get a full universe of prices?":"Yahoo Finance 对批量下载限流。你怎么把一整个股票池的价格拉下来的?","pulling 1y daily bars for ~550 S&P 500 + Nasdaq 100 names gets throttled or returns empties from yfinance.":"为约 550 个 S&P 500 + Nasdaq 100 标的拉一年日线,yfinance 要么被限流,要么返回空。","per-ticker loops (slow, hits limits) and plain bulk download (gets blocked).":"逐个标的循环(慢,还撞限额),以及直接批量下载(被封)。","one batched download over a":"一次批量下载,走在一个","session with":"会话上,配","so the requests look like a real browser — that session is the key fix for the rate-limits. Finnhub fundamentals are throttled separately at 1.1s/call (≤60/min) with a dedicated retry wrapper for HTTP 429.":",让请求看起来像个真浏览器——这个会话就是解限流的关键。Finnhub 的基本面数据单独限速,1.1 秒一次(≤60/分),配了个专门针对 HTTP 429 的重试包装。","Backtests lie. How do you keep a strategy honest before trusting it?":"回测会骗人。在信一个策略之前,你怎么让它保持诚实?","it's trivially easy to write an intraday backtest that shows big profit and is pure fiction — because it ignored commissions and slippage, or leaked future data into the entry.":"写一个显示大赚、却纯属虚构的日内回测,轻而易举——因为它忽略了佣金和滑点,或者把未来数据泄漏进了入场判断。","early backtests with no cost model. Numbers looked great and were meaningless.":"早期的回测没有成本模型。数字很好看,但毫无意义。","How I solved it — two guards:":"怎么解的——两道护栏:","Stage 0 \"Honest Engine\"":"Stage 0「诚实引擎」","runs before any strategy logic: it picks a few random trades, prints the full cost breakdown, and":"在任何策略逻辑之前先跑:它随机挑几笔交易,打印完整的成本拆解,并","that net P&L actually equals gross minus cost — the run raises if the cost model isn't wired in. No strategy gets evaluated until costs are provably deducted.":"净 P&L 确实等于毛利减成本——成本模型没接上,这次运行就抛错。在成本被可证明地扣掉之前,任何策略都不会被评估。","No look-ahead:":"无未来函数:","entry is decided from the first two composite bars only; the exit loop scans only bars strictly after entry. Plus a safety check that take-profit distance ≥ stop distance, which raises if violated.":"入场只由前两根合成 K 线决定;出场循环只扫描严格晚于入场的 K 线。再加一道安全检查:止盈距离 ≥ 止损距离,违反就抛错。","Backtest P&L looked good but you still didn't go live. What was the check?":"回测 P&L 看着不错,你却还是没上实盘。那道关卡是什么?","a strategy that \"wins\" on paper can still be one you shouldn't trade — too few trades, one lucky month, a single symbol carrying it.":"一个在纸面上「赢」的策略,仍可能是不该拿去交易的——交易太少、就靠某个走运的月份、或者全靠单一个标的撑着。","a separate":"一个独立的","review agent":"review agent","is a required pre-live gate — every strategy must pass it before it's allowed to run live. It ingests the results and trades CSVs and generates a \"challenge report\" that deliberately hunts for weaknesses (concentration, drawdown, schema quirks) instead of celebrating the headline return. It even normalizes two different result-CSV schemas so old and new runs can be compared. A strategy doesn't graduate on a good return alone; it graduates by surviving the challenge report.":"是上实盘前的必过关卡——每个策略在被允许实盘之前都得过它。它吃进结果和交易的 CSV,生成一份「挑战报告」,刻意去挖弱点(集中度、回撤、schema 的怪癖),而不是给头条收益率喝彩。它甚至会把两种不同的结果 CSV schema 归一化,好让新旧运行能对比。一个策略不靠收益好就毕业;它靠熬过挑战报告才毕业。","The daily news pulls the same story from five sources. How do you dedupe?":"每日新闻会从五个源拉到同一条报道。你怎么去重?","WSJ, MarketWatch and Google News all carry the same headline with different URLs — the digest fills up with duplicates.":"WSJ、MarketWatch 和 Google News 都载着同一条头条,URL 却各不相同——摘要里全是重复。","dedupe by URL. Doesn't work — same story, different URLs.":"按 URL 去重。行不通——同一条报道,URL 不一样。","two-layer dedup — exact URL hash plus fuzzy title matching (ratio ≥ 85), so near-identical headlines from different outlets collapse to one. Collection itself is concurrent with a per-day cache so re-runs are cheap, and each source failure is caught and logged instead of killing the batch.":"两层去重——URL 精确哈希,加上标题模糊匹配(ratio ≥ 85),这样不同媒体那些几乎一样的头条就会塌缩成一条。抓取本身是并发的,配了按天缓存,所以重跑很便宜;每个源的失败都被捕获并记日志,而不是把整批搞挂。","Timezones: you're in Malaysia trading US markets. What broke?":"时区:你人在马来西亚,交易美股。哪里出过问题?","\"yesterday's session,\" \"earnings in N days,\" and \"last completed session\" are all wrong if you compute them in local time — the US market runs overnight my time and shifts with US daylight saving, and there are US holidays.":"「昨天那节」「N 天后财报」「最近一节收盘」,只要用本地时间去算就全错——美股在我这边是隔夜跑的,还跟着美国夏令时挪动,加上美国的假期。","all trading-day logic computes in US/Eastern using an NYSE calendar (":"所有交易日逻辑都用 NYSE 日历、按 US/Eastern 算(","), never hardcoded offsets; \"last completed session\" is the most recent closed NYSE session, which handles weekends and holidays. Only the cron schedule is expressed in local time. Fail-safe rule: an unknown earnings date pauses swing trading on that name.":"),绝不硬编码偏移量;「最近一节收盘」取的是最近一节已收盘的 NYSE session,周末和假期都能处理。只有 cron 的排程用本地时间表示。兜底规则:财报日期未知,就暂停这只票的波段交易。","Config-vs-secret discipline: what belongs in the code and what doesn't?":"配置与密钥的分寸:什么该进代码,什么不该?","early on, two things that should have been configuration were baked into source — a personal notification target, and an API-required contact identifier (SEC EDGAR mandates a contact string in the request's User-Agent).":"早期,有两样本该是配置的东西被写死进了源码——一个私人的通知目标,以及一个 API 要求的联系人标识(SEC EDGAR 强制要求请求的 User-Agent 里带一个联系字符串)。","moved both to environment variables. The notification target now returns nothing and safely no-ops if unset; the SEC contact reads from an env var with a neutral placeholder default (the API requires":"两样都挪到了环境变量。通知目标现在没设置就返回空、安全地空转;SEC 联系人从一个环境变量读,默认值是个中性的占位串(API 要求有","string, so it can't be blank). Every repo's HEAD is clean — all secrets and personal identifiers load from env or a gitignored":"个字符串,所以不能留空)。每个 repo 的 HEAD 都是干净的——所有密钥和私人标识都从环境变量或 gitignore 掉的","The lesson:":"教训:","the distinction that matters isn't \"secret vs public\" — it's":"真正要紧的区分,不是「密钥 vs 公开」,而是","\"does this identify a person or a machine?\"":"「这东西是不是指向了某个人或某台机器?」","An API-required field like a contact email still needs to be config, not a hardcoded default, because the default leaks":"像联系邮箱这种 API 要求的字段,仍然得是配置,而不是硬编码的默认值,因为那个默认值泄漏的是",". And a removal commit is not a fix: once something is in version-control history, only a history rewrite plus credential rotation actually removes it.":"。而且一次删除提交不算修复:东西一旦进了版本控制历史,只有重写历史加轮换凭证,才是真的把它清掉。","asserts":"断言","repos":"repo","the code":"代码","The three":"三个","The three repos, as evidence. Recommend-only — every order is placed by hand.":"这三个 repo,作为证据。只推荐——每一笔订单都是手动下的。","— the daily news aggregator.":"——每日新闻聚合器。","— the live daily assistant.":"——每日实时助手。","— offline research and validation.":"——离线研究与验证。","Work":"工作","Lab":"实验室","Notes":"笔记","Contact":"联系","ai engineering":"AI 工程","Engineering":"工程","Using AI well is an engineering discipline, not a habit. I built my team's AI delivery system — the pipeline, the gates, the context, the review roles — and it ships real features.":"用好 AI 是一门工程学科,不是一个习惯。我团队的 AI 交付体系是我搭的——pipeline、门禁、context、review 角色——它交付的是真实的功能。","10 pipeline stages":"10 个 pipeline 阶段","16 features shipped through it":"16 个功能经它上线","30+ per-service context files":"32 份按服务的 context 文件","4 role-based AI reviewers":"4 个按角色分工的 AI reviewer","feature drafts: days → hours":"功能初稿:数天 → 数小时","the failure file":"失败档案","The failure":"失败","file":"档案","Every AI success story you'll read is missing this section. Here's what went wrong in ours — the discipline came from the failures.":"你读到的每一个 AI 成功故事,都缺了这一节。这是我们这套体系里出过的错——纪律正是从失败里长出来的。","The fix that broke production":"把生产搞坏的那次修复","The agent found a real bug — one that had sat harmless in production for years — and repaired it. The repair changed behavior other code had quietly grown to depend on, and things blew up. Lesson: an agent evaluates code; it doesn't know your system's history. A harmless bug is load-bearing until proven otherwise.":"agent 找到了一个真 bug——在生产上无害地躺了好几年——然后把它修了。这一修,改掉了其他代码早已悄悄依赖的行为,东西就炸了。教训:agent 评估的是代码,它不知道你系统的历史。一个无害的 bug,在证明之前都要当它是承重的。","The big answer to a small ask":"小需求,大答案","The requirement was genuinely small — an existing rule needed one more condition, a change the codebase was already shaped for. The agent, not grasping that intent, rebuilt the surrounding flow instead: hundreds of new lines that technically worked and doubled the review burden. Lesson: the smallest correct change comes from knowing what the codebase already wants to do — that judgment is still ours.":"需求真的很小——给一条现有规则多加一个条件,代码库本来就是为这种改动准备的。agent 没抓住这层意图,把周边的流程重建了一遍:几百行新代码,技术上能跑,review 负担翻倍。教训:最小的正确改动,来自知道代码库本来想怎么做——这个判断仍然在我们手上。","Correct, and slow":"正确,但慢","Asked for accuracy, the agent updated the database row by row — correct, and an IO storm at our volume. Batching was the obvious answer, but only obvious to someone who has paid for IO before. Lesson: performance instincts don't ship with the model; they come from the scars.":"要求它保证准确,agent 就一行一行地更新数据库——正确,但在我们的量级上是一场 IO 风暴。批量处理是显而易见的答案,可只对为 IO 付过学费的人显而易见。教训:性能直觉不随模型出厂,它来自伤疤。","The pattern behind all three: the damage happens when someone can't yet tell a good answer from a plausible one — a junior burning tokens on the wrong question, merging changes they can't explain. So the rule is not \"use AI less.\" It is:":"三件事背后是同一个模式:当一个人还分不出「好答案」和「像样的答案」时,伤害就发生了——junior 在错误的问题上烧 token,merge 自己解释不了的改动。所以规则不是「少用 AI」,而是:","discernment first, delegation second":"先有判断力,再谈委派",". You must be able to judge the problem and the logic before you outsource the typing.":"。你得先能评判问题和逻辑,才能把打字外包出去。","the delivery system":"交付体系","The delivery":"交付","system":"体系","An artifact-gated, 10-stage delivery pipeline built as agent skills: requirements document (PRD) → design → contracts → SDK → tasks → parallel agent development → machine-judged acceptance. Every artifact carries a human approval signature, and irreversible actions — publish, push, migrations — require explicit human confirmation.":"一条以产物为门禁、10 个阶段的交付 pipeline,用 agent skills 搭起来:需求文档(PRD)→ 设计 → 契约 → SDK → 任务 → 多 agent 并行开发 → 机器判定验收。每份产物都带人工批准签名,不可逆的动作——publish、push、migration——必须由人明确确认。","Artifact Pipeline":"产物 pipeline","Role-based Review":"按角色 review","Human Gates":"人工门禁","Team-built AI incident diagnoser living in our team chat: symptoms in, trace-backed hypotheses out — reading production logs over MCP and code across every repo, frontend and backend. The real work was making the system diagnosable first: standardized errors, trace IDs through every hop, names that tell you what broke. The bot is the payoff; the discipline is the design.":"团队自建的 AI 事故诊断器,住在团队 chat 里:症状进,带 trace 佐证的假设出——通过 MCP 读生产日志,读遍每个仓库的代码,前端后端都在内。真正的功夫是先把系统变得可诊断:标准化的错误、贯穿每一跳的 trace ID、一看就知道坏在哪的命名。bot 是回报,纪律才是设计。","Standardized Tracing":"标准化 tracing","Event Schema Registry":"事件 Schema Registry","JSON-Schema-first event contracts with multi-language SDK codegen (Node, Java, Rust) — producers and consumers can't drift because the schema is the source of truth.":"JSON-Schema 先行的事件契约,配多语言 SDK 代码生成(Node、Java、Rust)——schema 就是唯一事实来源,生产者和消费者想漂移也漂移不了。","Codegen":"代码生成","Multi-language SDK":"多语言 SDK","Operations agent (human-in-the-loop)":"运营 agent(human-in-the-loop)","A LangChain agent living in our team chat: operations asks in natural language, the agent resolves the target audience, shows a preview, and executes only after an explicit \"confirm\" — every step audit-logged. The same gate philosophy as everything else I build.":"一个住在团队 chat 里的 LangChain agent:运营用自然语言提需求,agent 解析出目标用户群,先给预览,收到明确的「confirm」才执行——每一步都留审计日志。和我做的其他东西,同一套门禁哲学。","Preview-first":"预览先行","Context engineering":"Context 工程","Clever prompts don't scale; engineered context does — a routing manifest across 17 repositories, 30+ per-service context files, and persistent memory across sessions. The agent starts every task already knowing the codebase.":"巧妙的 prompt 撑不起规模,工程化的 context 才行——一份横跨 17 个仓库的路由清单、32 份按服务的 context 文件,加上跨 session 的持久记忆。agent 接到任何任务时,已经认识这套代码库了。","Routing Manifest":"路由清单","Context Files":"Context 文件","Persistent Memory":"持久记忆","working with agents":"与 agent 协作","Principles of working with":"与 agent 协作的","agents":"原则","AI proposes, humans approve.":"AI 提议,人来批准。","Every irreversible action — commit, publish, deploy, migration — sits behind an explicit human gate. No agent ever commits.":"每一个不可逆的动作——commit、publish、部署、migration——都在一道明确的人工门禁后面。任何 agent 都不许 commit。","AI compresses the zero-to-eighty stretch.":"AI 压缩的是从零到八十的那段路。","A two-day build becomes a two-hour first draft. The last twenty percent is still ours, and the real skill is discernment: catching what it got wrong.":"两天的活变成两小时的初稿。最后那百分之二十仍然归我们,真正的本事是判断力:抓出它做错的地方。","AI amplifies your code culture.":"AI 放大你的代码文化。","Rot in, rot out — an agent raised on a disciplined codebase ships discipline; raised on mess, it ships mess faster.":"喂进去什么,长出来什么——在有纪律的代码库里养大的 agent,交付纪律;在烂摊子里养大的,只会更快地交付烂摊子。","Context beats prompts.":"Context 胜过 prompt。","The agent should start every task already knowing the codebase — routing manifests, per-service context files, persistent memory — not a cleverly worded request.":"agent 接到任务时就该已经认识代码库——路由清单、按服务的 context 文件、持久记忆——而不是靠一句措辞巧妙的请求。","Incidents compile into policy.":"事故要编译成规矩。","A production lesson becomes a rule wired into the agent harness — a readiness gate the agent can't skip, so the same mistake can't ship twice.":"一次生产教训变成写进 agent harness 的规则——一道 agent 跳不过的就绪门禁,同一个错误就不可能上线第二次。","the rules":"规矩","The rules my agents":"我的 agent 要守的","live by":"规矩","Both of my agents — the one at work and the one at home — run under the same standing rules. Every one of them was written the hard way.":"我的两个 agent——公司那个和家里那个——跑在同一套长期规则下。每一条都是踩过坑才写下来的。","Rule 0: no guessing.":"规则 0:不许猜。","Verify before speaking; if you can't verify, say so.":"先验证再开口;验证不了,就直说验证不了。","My words mean exactly what they say.":"我的话就是字面意思。","Don't interpret, don't complete my thoughts — ask.":"不要解读,不要替我补完想法——问。","Execute only what was asked.":"只执行被要求的事。","\"While I'm here, let me also…\" is where incidents start.":"「顺手把这个也……」正是事故的起点。","Show proof after every write.":"每次写入后都要给证据。","\"Done\" is a claim; a file path is evidence.":"「做完了」是一句主张,文件路径才是证据。","Discussion is not permission.":"讨论不等于许可。","Talking about running something is not approval to run it.":"聊到要跑某个东西,不等于批准去跑。","\"It ran\" is not \"it works.\"":"「跑过了」不等于「跑对了」。","Verify after every execution.":"每次执行后都要验证。","Slow is fine.":"慢不要紧,","Wrong is not.":"错不行。","raising an agent":"养 agent","Raising an":"养一个","The Lab page shows what my home agent does. This is how it got that way — the same method I use on the agents at work, run twice, converging on the same constitution.":"实验室那页展示的是我家里那个 agent 会做什么。这一页讲它是怎么长成这样的——和我在公司调教 agent 用的是同一套方法,跑了两遍,收敛出同一部宪法。","Constitution before tasks":"先立宪法,再派活","On day two of the agent's life I installed SOUL.md — its identity file: problem-solving protocol, naming rules, behavioral law — before it did any real work. Rules don't retrofit well.":"agent 出生的第二天,我就给它装上了 SOUL.md——它的身份文件:解题协议、命名规则、行为法——在它干任何正经活之前。规矩这种东西,事后补装是装不牢的。","Small jobs first":"小活先行","New agent, small scope. I watch where it stalls or overreaches, then widen. It's the same calibrated-challenge ladder I use on junior engineers.":"新 agent,只 delegate 小范围的活。我盯着它在哪儿卡壳、在哪儿越界,再逐步放宽。这和我带 junior 工程师用的,是同一把校准过难度的阶梯。","Every failure becomes law, immediately":"失败即立法,当天生效","It executed without confirmation three times in one session — that same day, \"discussion is not permission\" became permanent law. Six standing rules; every one has an incident behind it.":"一个 session 里,它三次没等确认就执行——当天,「讨论不等于许可」就成了永久法条。六条长期规则,每一条背后都有一次事故。","Writes must show receipts":"写入要出示证据","After every correction the agent must show the stored entry — ID and content. \"Got it\" is not evidence that learning happened.":"每次纠正之后,agent 必须把存进去的条目亮出来——ID 和内容。一句「记住了」,不能证明学习真的发生过。","Memory has an economy":"记忆有经济学","Every always-loaded fact costs tokens forever, so MEMORY.md — the always-loaded layer — has a 7-day admission test: still true and useful in a week, or it doesn't get in. Facts route by weight — behavioral law loads every turn, Mnemosyne holds the long tail for on-demand recall, transcripts stay searchable but out of the way.":"每一条常驻加载的事实都要永远付 token 成本,所以 MEMORY.md——常驻加载的那一层——设了「7 天准入测试」:一周后还真、还有用,才准进。事实按分量分流——行为法每一轮都加载,Mnemosyne 存放长尾、按需召回,聊天记录可搜索,但不占道。","Tune the harness, not just the prompt":"连 harness 一起调,不只调 prompt","The expensive model was over-serving simple execution, so it got demoted to deep-reasoning duty only. An update wiped the config once — pre-update backups went on that day. A nightly memory digest, a weekly consolidation pass, a monthly self-audit: the agent maintains itself, on a schedule.":"贵的模型被过度用在简单执行上,于是降级为只值 deep-reasoning 的班。一次更新抹掉过一回 config——当天就加上了更新前备份。每晚一份记忆 digest,每周一轮整合,每月一次自查:agent 按日程维护它自己。","Two agents, two independent memory stores, one converging constitution. That's when you know it's a method — not a habit.":"两个 agent,两套独立记忆,收敛出同一部宪法——这时候你才知道,这是方法,不是习惯。","the constraints":"约束","Every tool answers a":"每个工具都在回答一个","constraint":"约束","None of this tooling exists because it's cool. Large language models have a handful of hard constraints — and every piece of my stack is a direct answer to one of them.":"这些工具没有一样是因为\"酷\"才存在的。大语言模型有几条绕不开的硬约束——我的每一件工具,都是对其中一条的直接回答。","Context is finite":"上下文是有限的","A model can only hold so much, so relevance beats volume: a routing manifest across 17 repositories decides where a task belongs, and 30+ per-service context files mean the agent starts already knowing the codebase — instead of re-reading it every session.":"模型装不下所有东西,所以\"相关\"比\"多\"重要:一份覆盖 17 个 repo 的路由清单决定任务归哪里,30+ 份 per-service context 文件让 agent 一开工就认识代码库——而不是每个 session 重新读一遍。","Memory doesn't persist":"记忆不会自己留下","The biggest handicap of any agent: session ends, knowledge gone. My answer is layered — an identity file for law, an always-loaded fact file with a 7-day admission test, a vector store (Mnemosyne, 3,700+ entries) for the long tail, and Obsidian as the human-curated layer on top. Facts route by weight; nothing important lives in only one head.":"agent 最大的残障:session 一结束,知识就没了。我的答案是分层——身份文件放\"法律\",常驻事实文件设 7 天准入测试,向量库(Mnemosyne,3,700+ 条)接长尾,Obsidian 做人工沉淀层。事实按权重路由;重要的东西绝不只活在一个脑袋里。","Tokens aren't free":"token 不是免费的","Every dev command an agent runs burns context. A filtering proxy (RTK) strips the noise before the model sees it — 75M+ tokens measured saved. Scheduled scripts that need no judgment run with no LLM at all. At home, a tiered router sends routine work to budget models and saves the heavyweight for deep reasoning. Same principle at every scale: pay for thinking, not for typing.":"agent 跑的每条 dev 命令都在烧上下文。一层过滤代理(RTK)在模型看到之前把噪音剥掉——实测省下 75M+ tokens。不需要判断的定时任务干脆不用 LLM 跑。在家里,分层路由把日常活派给便宜模型,重推理才请重型选手。同一个原则贯穿所有尺度:为思考付钱,不为打字付钱。","Plausible is not correct":"像样 ≠ 正确","Models produce answers that look right. That's why nothing merges without a human gate, every memory write shows a receipt, and the failure file above exists. Trust is a budget — spend it on verification, not on hope.":"模型产出的是\"看起来对\"的答案。所以任何东西不过人工闸门不许 merge,每次记忆写入都要出示收据,上面那份失败档案也因此存在。信任是预算——花在验证上,不要花在侥幸上。","Good process doesn't repeat itself":"好流程不该重复自己","Anything done twice becomes a versioned skill. Some we adopted from the community and adapted — credited, not claimed. Some we built from scratch: the delivery pipeline, the review roles, the repo router. The test is always the same: would a new teammate — human or agent — do this right on day one?":"做过两遍的事就该变成有版本的 skill。有些是从社区拿来再改造的——署名,不冒领;有些是从零自建的:交付管线、角色评审、repo 路由。检验标准永远是同一条:一个新同事——不管是人还是 agent——第一天照着做,能不能做对?","The stack will change. The constraints won't.":"工具会换,约束不会。","Build for the constraints.":"为约束而建。","featured work":"精选工作","Featured":"精选","Case 01":"案例 01","Case 02":"案例 02","Case 03":"案例 03","Index first, cache second":"先索引,后缓存","how i work":"我怎么工作","How I":"我怎么","about":"关于","About":"关于","me":"我","core stack":"核心技术栈","TypeScript · NestJS · gRPC · MongoDB · Redis · Temporal · Pulsar —":"TypeScript · NestJS · gRPC · MongoDB · Redis · Temporal · Pulsar ——","full tiers →":"完整分层 →","contact":"联系","Get in":"联系","touch":"我","personal lab":"个人实验室","Personal":"个人","What I build when nobody's paying me to.":"没人付钱我也在做的东西。","Hermes — a self-hosted agent":"Hermes——一个 self-hosted 的 agent","Hermes Agent — Nous Research's open-source framework — running bare in WSL2 on my home server since May 2026, reachable through Telegram and WhatsApp gateways. Memory is layered: SOUL.md / MEMORY.md / USER.md carry identity and standing law (a fact must survive a 7-day admission test to get in), while Mnemosyne — vector memory on SQLite + embeddings — holds 3,700+ entries and counting for on-demand recall. 73 skills and 7 cron jobs do real work: a daily news brief, pre-market trading levels, a nightly memory digest, weekly memory consolidation, a monthly self-audit — and it built and maintains this very site. Same rule as at work: the agent does the miles, a human owns the gate.":"Hermes Agent——Nous Research 的开源框架——自 2026 年 5 月起裸装在我家用服务器的 WSL2 里,通过 Telegram 和 WhatsApp 网关随叫随到。记忆是分层的:SOUL.md / MEMORY.md / USER.md 承载身份和长期法条(一条事实要通过「7 天准入测试」才准进),Mnemosyne——建在 SQLite + embeddings 上的向量记忆——存着 3,700+ 条还在涨的条目,按需召回。73 个 skills 和 7 个 cron 任务干的是真活:每日新闻简报、开盘前交易点位、每晚记忆 digest、每周记忆整合、每月自查——这个网站也是它做的、它在维护。和公司里同一条规则:路让 agent 跑,门归人来把。","73 skills":"73 个 skills","3.7k+ memories":"3.7k+ 条记忆","7 cron jobs":"7 个 cron 任务","running since May 2026":"自 2026 年 5 月运行至今","Mnemosyne memory":"Mnemosyne 记忆","Scalp analyzer":"Scalp 分析器","A live US-stock scalping analyzer in Python, run against a local Moomoo OpenD instance with yfinance as the fallback feed. It pulls 1m/5m/15m candles, computes EMA/MACD/RSI and session-anchored VWAP with pandas + ta, and checks seven classic setups — opening-range breakout, VWAP bounce, bull flag — with a confluence checklist and a 0–10 safety score that penalizes lunch chop and fading momentum. Wired up as a Claude Code skill, so \"check NVDA\" returns an entry/target/stop card. The pipeline is deliberately linear — feed → candles → checks → score → card — so when a reading looks wrong there is exactly one stage to inspect. Analysis only — every order is placed by hand.":"一个用 Python 写的美股 scalp 实时分析器,对着本地 Moomoo OpenD 实例跑,yfinance 做兜底数据源。它拉 1m/5m/15m K 线,用 pandas + ta 算 EMA/MACD/RSI 和以当日开盘锚定的 VWAP,检查七种经典形态——开盘区间突破、VWAP 反弹、bull flag——配一张 confluence 清单和一个 0–10 的安全分,午间震荡和动能衰减都会扣分。包装成了 Claude Code skill,一句「check NVDA」就返回一张 entry/target/stop 卡片。pipeline 刻意做成线性——feed → candles → checks → score → card——读数不对时,要查的环节只会有一个。只做分析——每一笔订单都是手动下的。","yfinance fallback":"yfinance 兜底","Stock sentry":"股票哨兵","My biggest personal build: an AI trading assistant living in Telegram — python-telegram-bot at the front, the OpenAI API behind a multi-agent pipeline — analyzer, technical analyst, strategy generator, backtester, final decision — with Finnhub and yfinance for market data, a Streamlit backoffice, deployed on Zeabur. The agents run as a fixed chain — each one's output is the next one's input — so a verdict is traceable back through the backtest, strategy and analysis stages that produced it. Strategies live in a JSON skill library: the orchestrator matches them to market conditions, ranks them by tracked performance, and feeds trade outcomes back in. Every answer is forced into a tight format: verdict, entry, target, stop, one reason. About 8k lines of Python.":"我最大的个人项目:一个住在 Telegram 里的 AI 交易助手——前面是 python-telegram-bot,后面是 OpenAI API 驱动的多 agent pipeline——分析器、技术分析、策略生成、回测、最终决策——行情数据来自 Finnhub 和 yfinance,配一个 Streamlit 后台,部署在 Zeabur 上。agent 按固定链条跑——上一个的输出就是下一个的输入——所以每个结论都能沿着产生它的回测、策略、分析各阶段追回去。策略放在一个 JSON skill 库里:orchestrator 按市场状态匹配策略,按跟踪到的表现排序,再把交易结果喂回去。每个回答都被强制成紧凑格式:结论、entry、target、stop、一条理由。约 8k 行 Python。","AI home server":"AI 家用服务器","No longer a blueprint — a Minisforum UM890 Pro (Ryzen 9 8945HS, 32GB) now runs 24/7 in my living room: Windows 11 with WSL2 Ubuntu, Hermes installed bare-metal inside, plus a FastAPI trading server and a static daily-news page. Access is Tailscale-only — zero open ports, with a Windows portproxy bridging into WSL. The honest lesson: local models were the plan, and they lost — Ollama running Qwen 2.5 7B and Llama 3.1 8B couldn't keep up with multi-round tool calling on CPU-only inference, so a tiered router now sends routine work to budget cloud models and reserves a heavyweight for deep reasoning. The security model survived contact intact: sandboxed agent, outbound allowlist, low-privilege accounts per service, and a green/yellow/red delegation table — banking credentials stay red, forever.":"已经不是蓝图了——一台 Minisforum UM890 Pro(Ryzen 9 8945HS,32GB)现在 24/7 跑在我的客厅里:Windows 11 加 WSL2 Ubuntu,Hermes 裸装在里面,外加一个 FastAPI 交易服务和一个静态每日新闻页。访问只走 Tailscale——零开放端口,由 Windows portproxy 桥进 WSL。诚实的教训:本地模型本来是计划,但它们输了——Ollama 跑 Qwen 2.5 7B 和 Llama 3.1 8B,纯 CPU 推理跟不上多轮 tool calling,所以现在由一个分层 router 把日常工作发给便宜的云端模型,把重型模型留给深度推理。安全模型倒是完好地经受住了现实:沙箱里的 agent、出站白名单、每个服务一个低权限账号,以及一张绿/黄/红委派表——银行凭证永远是红,永远。","Tailscale-only":"仅 Tailscale 可达","Ollama → tiered cloud":"Ollama → 分层云端","24/7 since May 2026":"24/7,自 2026 年 5 月","Personal financial planning system":"个人财务规划系统","View on GitHub ↗":"在 GitHub 查看 ↗","200+ types · one base workflow":"200+ 种类型 · 一条 base workflow","Outcome":"结果","audited lifecycle — every transaction":"audited lifecycle — every transaction","The redemption that didn't charge":"没扣费的那次兑换","The signal that arrived too early":"来得太早的 signal","The retry that had to return the same record":"必须拿回同一条记录的 retry","Four environments, one engine":"四个环境,一个引擎","← All work":"← 全部工作","Most of the work was comparing numbers":"大部分工作,是在对数字","Nobody tells you this about building an ingestion pipeline: the code is the quick part. For a long stretch of development, one record subtype ran as a permanent probe — continuously reconciled against its sources while everything else was still moving.":"做接入 pipeline,没人告诉你的一件事是:写代码是快的那部分。开发过程中有很长一段时间,一种记录子类型作为常驻探针在跑——在其他一切还在动的时候,持续和它的来源对账。","Then the cross-checks widened: daily totals per record type compared against the analytics team's independent numbers, and per-user daily histories diffed record by record. When a figure disagreed, that was the day's work — trace which source dropped, duplicated or reshaped it, fix the boundary, backfill, compare again.":"然后交叉核对越铺越宽:每种记录类型的每日总数,对上分析团队独立算出的数字;每个用户的每日历史,逐条 diff。哪个数字对不上,那就是当天的活——追出是哪个来源丢了、重复了还是改了形状,修好边界,backfill,再对一遍。","It's manual, it's unglamorous, and it's the only reason the number on a user's screen can be trusted. Correctness isn't a property you declare; it's one you keep re-earning.":"这活儿手工、不体面,但用户屏幕上那个数字之所以可信,靠的就是它。正确性不是一个宣布了就成立的属性,而是要不断重新挣来的。","Measure first, then argue":"先测量,再争论","The revert that came back stronger":"回来更强的那次 revert","The day the cluster said no":"集群说「不」的那天","Queue positions lived as scores, and the original update was read-modify-write: read the score, compute in memory, write it back. Under concurrency two updates interleaved and one silently overwrote the other. I rebuilt the updates as atomic increments wrapped in a transaction — and then production revealed our Redis cluster wouldn't accept the transaction at all. Because the score design was banded — status, load and waiting time each own their own order of magnitude — every state change was already expressible as a single atomic increment, so we degraded to pure atomic ops the same day. A fix isn't done until it survives the real topology — and data designed for plan B is why the fallback was a same-day change, not a redesign.":"队列位置以分数的形式存着,最初的更新是 read-modify-write:读出分数、内存里算、写回去。并发之下两次更新交错,一次悄悄覆盖了另一次。我把更新重建成包在事务里的原子自增——结果生产环境揭示,我们的 Redis cluster 根本不接受这个事务。好在分数设计从一开始就是分段的——状态、负载、等待时长各占一个数量级——每一次状态变化本来就能表达成一次单独的原子自增,所以我们当天就降级成了纯原子操作。一个修复,要在真实拓扑上活下来才算完——而为 plan B 设计过的数据,正是这次回退只是一个当天的改动、而不是一次重构的原因。","Two agents, one conversation":"两个客服,一场对话","Two messages arriving in the same conversation at the same moment each decided a human agent was needed — and two agents got invited into one chat. The fence is a per-room lock: the first caller takes it and performs the invite, everyone else finds it held and walks away, and the lock's time-to-live is aligned to the operation so a crash can't leave the room locked forever. Anything triggered by \"a message arrived\" will eventually be triggered twice in the same millisecond — design for the second caller before it exists.":"同一时刻落进同一个会话的两条消息,各自判断需要转人工——于是两个客服被邀进了同一个聊天。围栏是一把 per-room 锁:第一个调用者拿到锁、执行邀请,其他人发现锁被占就直接走开,锁的存活时间(TTL)对齐操作时长,崩溃也不会把房间永远锁死。任何由「来了一条消息」触发的东西,总有一天会在同一毫秒被触发两次——在第二个调用者出现之前,就为它做设计。","The model is a dependency you can't trust":"模型是一个不能信任的依赖","millions/day":"数百万/天","10M+/day · dual-stream join":"上千万/天 · dual-stream join","roads not taken":"没有走的路","Roads not":"没有走的","taken":"路","Every architecture I run replaced one I personally operated. Here's what lost, and why.":"我现在跑的每一套架构,都替换掉了一套我亲手维护过的。这里是落选者,和它们输掉的原因。","Cron and scan, versus durable workflows":"Cron 加扫描,还是 durable workflow","The old platform ran 22+ cron jobs, one of them re-scanning for stuck approvals every single minute. I maintained that for six years — so when durable workflows arrived, I didn't need a blog post to explain why retries belong in the engine, not in a scanner. What would change my mind: a workload where every task is truly fire-and-forget.":"旧平台跑着 22+ 个 cron job,其中一个每分钟重扫一遍卡住的审批。这套东西我维护了六年——所以 durable workflow 一来,不需要谁写博客来说服我:retry 应该住在引擎里,而不是扫描器里。什么会让我改主意:一个所有任务都真正 fire-and-forget 的场景。","Tune the database harder, versus add a cache":"把数据库调得更狠,还是加一层缓存","Redis was not the first answer — months of index work, aggregation rewrites and dead-index deletion came first. The cache earned its place only after the database was already honest. What would change my mind: nothing; the order itself is the principle.":"Redis 不是第一个答案——先来的是几个月的 index 功课、aggregation 重写、删掉死 index。等数据库已经诚实了,缓存才配拿到自己的位置。什么会让我改主意:没有;这个顺序本身就是原则。","The benchmark that lost, then won":"输掉的 benchmark,后来赢了","An analytics engine failed our JSON-path queries — 3 to 15 times slower. Instead of accepting the verdict, we flattened the schema and removed the weakness, and the verdict changed. Benchmarks are inputs to architecture, not judges of it.":"一个分析型引擎在我们的 JSON-path 查询上败下阵来——慢 3 到 15 倍。我们没有接受判决,而是把 schema 拍平、移除弱点,判决就变了。Benchmark 是架构的输入,不是它的法官。","Local models, versus a tiered router":"本地模型,还是分层 tiered router","At home I wanted local models for everything — free, private, mine. CPU-only inference lost to multi-round tool calling by an order of magnitude, so a tiered router took its place. Losing cleanly beats winning on paper.":"在家里我什么都想用本地模型——免费、私有、属于我自己。CPU-only 推理在多轮 tool calling 上输了一个数量级,于是 tiered router 顶了上来。干脆地输,好过纸面上赢。","where this happened":"这些都发生在哪","Where this":"这些都发生在","happened":"哪","Dec 2019 – present · Malaysia":"2019 年 12 月 – 至今 · 马来西亚","A high-concurrency transaction platform":"一个高并发的 高并发交易平台","A five-person team owning six module domains across two generations of stack — legacy monolith and modern microservices — plus third-party service integrations. Architecture gatekeeper for cross-team requirements. I grow engineers through ownership — three juniors now run an entire production platform themselves. Weekly releases, CI/CD discipline, mentoring as the core of the job.":"一个五人团队,负责横跨两代技术栈的六个模块域——旧的单体和新的微服务——外加第三方服务集成。跨团队需求的架构把关人。我靠 ownership 培养工程师——三个 junior 现在自己撑起一个完整的生产平台。每周发版、CI/CD 纪律,mentoring 是这份工作的核心。","2,000+ merged pull requests, from full-stack on the legacy platform to pioneering the new stack. Highlights beyond the case studies: hardened withdrawal flows, peer-to-peer order matching (50+ pull requests in two months), session security, and third-party WebSocket integrations with heartbeat keep-alives. The SDK-per-domain pattern I pioneered for the workflow platform has since become the platform standard — a shared SDK layer of 14 packages, consumed by 8 services, built by the platform team on that model.":"2,000+ 个 merge 掉的 PR,从旧平台的全栈一路做到新技术栈的开荒。案例之外的亮点:加固提现流程、用户间订单撮合(两个月 50+ 个 PR)、会话安全,以及带心跳保活的第三方 WebSocket 集成。我为 workflow 平台开创的 SDK-per-domain 模式,如今成了平台标准——平台团队照这个模式建起了 14 个包的共享 SDK 层,8 个服务在用。","2018 – 2019 · Malaysia":"2018 – 2019 · 马来西亚","Mobile Engineer":"移动端工程师","Insurance point-of-sale hybrid app; automated the daily QA deployment.":"保险 POS 混合应用;把每天的 QA 部署自动化了。","Core (ships daily)":"核心(每天在用)","TypeScript · NestJS · gRPC / proto-first contracts · MongoDB (aggregation, indexing, Atlas Search) · Redis (data-structure design, cluster) · Temporal · Apache Pulsar · Jest + Testcontainers (real databases, not mocks)":"TypeScript · NestJS · gRPC / proto 先行的契约 · MongoDB(aggregation、索引、Atlas Search)· Redis(数据结构设计、cluster)· Temporal · Apache Pulsar · Jest + Testcontainers(跑真实数据库,不是 mock)","Working":"熟练","Java (Flink streaming jobs) · Rust (one full service — Temporal SDK, tonic/prost — pre-production) · Apache Flink (DataStream + SQL, managed) · ClickHouse · Hologres · PostgreSQL · HashiCorp Vault · OpenTelemetry · Grafana · Alibaba Cloud SLS (log forensics) · LangChain / LLM app development":"Java(Flink 流式作业)· Rust(一个完整服务——Temporal SDK、tonic/prost——pre-production)· Apache Flink(DataStream + SQL,托管版)· ClickHouse · Hologres · PostgreSQL · HashiCorp Vault · OpenTelemetry · Grafana · 阿里云 SLS(日志取证)· LangChain / LLM 应用开发","Familiar":"用过","Kafka · Node/Express legacy patterns · Socket.io / self-hosted messaging backbones · AngularJS-era stack · Docker · GitHub Actions · Alibaba Cloud (application level)":"Kafka · Node/Express 旧式模式 · Socket.io / 自托管 messaging backbone · AngularJS 时代的技术栈 · Docker · GitHub Actions · 阿里云(应用层)","Home lab":"家庭实验室","Short, practical lessons from operating production systems.":"来自运维生产系统的简短、实用经验。","Lead Software Engineer Dec 2025– · Senior Software Engineer 2024–2025 · Software Engineer 2019–2024":"Lead Software Engineer 2025-12 起 · Senior Software Engineer 2024–2025 · Software Engineer 2019–2024","live demo 01":"在线演示 01","live demo 02":"在线演示 02","live demo 03":"在线演示 03","Retry Storm":"重试风暴","Dispatch Floor":"调度大厅","Live GitHub":"GitHub 实况","Hammer one transaction with retries — the idempotency design refuses to execute it twice.":"用重试狂轰同一笔交易——幂等设计拒绝把它执行第二次。","Watch the routing queue pick the next agent — status first, load second, longest wait breaks the tie.":"看路由队列如何挑下一位客服——先看状态,再看负载,等最久者决胜。","See it live →":"看实况 →","© 2026 Henry Lee":"© 2026 Henry Lee","Email ↗":"邮件 ↗","LinkedIn ↗":"LinkedIn ↗","GitHub ↗":"GitHub ↗","execute":"执行","ledger ✓":"台账 ✓","retry ⟲":"重试 ⟲","field notes":"现场笔记","Field":"现场","The +1-billion offset":"领先 10 亿的偏移","One owner per number":"一个数字,一个 owner","Idempotency is a contract, not a patch":"幂等是契约,不是补丁","AI writes, humans gate":"AI 来写,人来把关","Handoff is a feature":"交接本身就是一项功能","One bare Server::serve() became a policy":"一句裸的 Server::serve() 换来一条规矩","What a lead watches":"一个 lead 每天盯什么","Repair scripts are production code":"修复脚本就是生产代码","Instead of coordinating a live cutover, make collisions impossible. Boring beats clever when transactions are on the line — the full story is in":"与其去编排一次线上 cutover,不如让碰撞根本不可能发生。当交易在盯着的时候,无聊胜过聪明——完整的故事在","the scaling case":"平台扩容那篇","A fix isn't done until it survives the real topology. The war story — a race fixed with MULTI, a cluster that refused it — lives in":"一个修复,要在真实拓扑上活下来才算完。那场实战——用 MULTI 修竞态,却被 cluster 拒绝——记在","the support case":"实时客服那篇","A threshold that lives in two systems will eventually disagree with itself, silently. We deleted the producer-side filter and left the number in exactly one place. Debugging is a graph search — fewer edges wins. The full chain is in":"一个同时活在两个系统里的阈值,迟早会和自己悄悄对不上。我们删掉了生产者那侧的过滤,让这个数字只留在一处。排查是一次图搜索——边越少越好。完整的链路在","the mission-pipeline case":"跨栈任务 pipeline 那篇","On transaction paths we assume every step will be retried, because someday it will be. Design for the retry and the 2am page never comes — the mechanics are in":"在资金路径上,我们假设每一步都会被 retry,因为总有一天它真会。为 retry 而设计,凌晨两点的告警就不会来——机制在","the backbone case":"交易主干那篇","The skill that matters is discernment — catching what the model got wrong before it merges. The full discipline, gates and failure file live on":"真正要紧的本事是判断力——在 merge 之前抓出模型做错的地方。完整的纪律、门禁和失败档案,都在","the AI page":"AI 那一页","If a system can't survive your absence, it isn't finished. Documentation, runbooks and self-service forms aren't chores; they're how you leave.":"一个系统如果撑不过你的缺席,它就还没做完。文档、runbook、自助表单不是杂活;它们是你离开的方式。","A service once shipped without signal handling — it died mid-request on every deploy. Graceful shutdown is now a readiness gate: any change touching a service entry point without the drain checklist gets blocked.":"有个服务上线时没处理信号——每次 deploy 都在请求中途暴毙。优雅停机现在是一道就绪门禁:任何动到服务入口、却没走排空清单的改动,一律拦下。","Every morning before standup: message-queue backlog depth, workflow-retry counts, the slow-query log, CPU and memory on the hot services — and the shape of a leak before it pages anyone. Dashboards in Grafana; log-based alerting and incident forensics in Aliyun SLS; OpenTelemetry traces and Prometheus metrics underneath. Not because watching is comforting — because every one of those curves has a story, and I want to hear it before the users do.":"每天站会前先看一遍:消息队列的积压深度、workflow 的重试次数、slow-query 日志、热点服务的 CPU 和内存——以及一次泄漏在惊动任何人之前的样子。看板在 Grafana;基于日志的告警和事故取证在阿里云 SLS;底层是 OpenTelemetry 链路和 Prometheus 指标。不是因为盯着让人安心——是因为每一条曲线背后都有一个故事,我想赶在用户之前听到它。","When transactions or data need backfilling, someone writes a \"one-off\" script at midnight. Ours aren't one-offs: batched, resumable, idempotent, dry-run first — because a repair script that fails halfway is a second incident. I've written more of these than I can count; the discipline is what keeps them boring.":"每当交易或数据需要 backfill,总有人在半夜写一个「一次性」脚本。我们的不是一次性的:分批、可续跑、幂等、默认先 dry-run——因为一个跑到一半失败的修复脚本,就是第二起事故。这种脚本我写过的数都数不清;正是这份纪律让它们保持无聊。","Before the platform earned its Redis layer, months went into the database itself: covering indexes matched to real query shapes, aggregation pipelines rebuilt stage by stage, full-text search where regex scans used to crawl. The fastest cache is the query that no longer needs one.":"在这个平台配得上它的 Redis 层之前,先花进去的是几个月的数据库功课:给真实的查询形状配上 covering index、把 aggregation pipeline 一段一段重建、把过去靠 regex 慢爬的地方换成全文搜索。最快的缓存,是那条不再需要缓存的查询。","A bilingual (EN / 中文) financial-planning app I built this year to run my own numbers: long-term financial projections at three lifestyle levels, mortgage-acceleration math, portfolio allocation with ten-year projections, and a cash & position tracker. Everything persists in localStorage with JSON export — no accounts, no server. Vanilla JavaScript, no framework — a tool for one user should stay simple enough to maintain in one evening.":"一个我今年做来算自己那本账的双语(EN / 中文)理财规划应用:三档生活水平下的长期财务推演、提前还房贷的算法、带十年推演的资产配置,外加一个现金与持仓追踪器。数据全部存在 localStorage、支持 JSON 导出——没有账号,没有服务器。纯 Vanilla JavaScript,不用框架——单人用的工具,就该简单到一个晚上能维护完。","gateways in · memory layered · jobs on schedule":"网关进来 · 记忆分层 · 任务按表跑","Hermes agent":"Hermes agent","identity in files · recall in vectors · work on cron":"身份在文件里 · 召回在向量里 · 活由 cron 跑","seven setups, one score, one card":"七种形态,一个分数,一张卡片","7 setup":"7 种形态","checks":"检查","0–10 safety score":"0–10 安全分","entry · target · stop":"入场 · 目标 · 止损","penalizes lunch chop · fading momentum":"午间震荡与动能衰减都扣分","analysis only — orders stay human":"只做分析——下单由人来","five agents, one verdict: entry · target · stop":"五个 agent,一个结论:入场 · 目标 · 止损","Telegram ask":"Telegram 提问","analyzer":"分析器","technical analyst":"技术分析","strategy generator":"策略生成","backtester":"回测","final decision":"最终决策","JSON skill library":"JSON 策略库","⇄ performance feedback":"⇄ 表现回流","matched to conditions · ranked by results · outcomes fed back":"按行情匹配 · 按结果排序 · 结果再喂回","one mini-PC, 24/7 in the living room":"一台迷你主机,7×24 待在客厅","Windows 11 host":"Windows 11 宿主","WSL2 Ubuntu":"WSL2 Ubuntu","FastAPI trading":"FastAPI 交易","news page":"新闻页","Ollama · retired":"Ollama · 已退役","✕ CPU-only, lost to cloud":"✕ 纯 CPU,败给云端","zero open ports · everything behind the VPN":"零开放端口 · 一切都在 VPN 之后","transaction":"交易","audited workflow":"带审计的 workflow","ledger ingestion":"台账接入","reconciliation probes":"对账探针","analytics sync":"分析同步","change data capture":"变更数据捕获","reports & filings":"报表与报送","1M rows/file":"每文件 100 万行","event bus":"事件总线","13 schemas · 3 SDKs":"13 份 schema · 3 个 SDK","growth pipeline":"增长 pipeline","exactly-once":"exactly-once","risk alerts":"风控告警","Python (pandas · FastAPI · Streamlit) · Telegram & WhatsApp bots · Tailscale · WSL2 · Ollama (local LLMs) · vector memory & embeddings · Zeabur":"Python(pandas · FastAPI · Streamlit)· Telegram 与 WhatsApp bot · Tailscale · WSL2 · Ollama(本地 LLM)· 向量记忆与 embeddings · Zeabur","detect → orchestrate → grant · boundaries follow existing seams":"发现 → 编排 → 发放 · 边界沿现有的缝走","detect + goals":"发现 + 目标","7-day workflow":"7 天 workflow","NestJS facade":"NestJS facade","grant":"发放","ledger · 1 / user·tier·month":"台账 · 每用户·等级·月 限 1 次","key · mission:user:tier:month":"key · mission:user:tier:month","legacy upgrade path · 0 changes":"走旧升级路径 · 0 改动","replace the mechanism, not the symptom":"换掉机制,而不是治症状","database counter":"数据库 counter","✕ serialized":"✕ 被串行化","Redis INCR · +1e9":"Redis INCR · +1e9","WebSocket fan-out":"WebSocket fan-out","✕ stalls":"✕ 卡死","pub/sub · N instances":"pub/sub · N 个实例","SMEMBERS":"SMEMBERS","✕ blocks":"✕ 阻塞","SSCAN cursors":"SSCAN 游标","shipped inside the weekly release train — users on, zero rewrites":"全程塞进每周发版的节奏里——用户在线,零重写","AI answers first — humans take the handoff":"AI 先答——由人接手交接","user msg":"用户消息","bot":"bot","answered · ~70%":"已答复 · ~70%","handoff · 10s guard":"交接 · 10 秒保护","zset queue · status ≫ load ≫ wait time":"zset 队列 · 状态 ≫ 负载 ≫ 等待时长","agent · O(1)":"客服 · O(1)","off-the-shelf backbone as transport — everything above it, built in-house":"现成底座只做传输——上面的一切,都自己建","create":"创建","review":"审核","approve":"批准","retry ⟲ returns the same record — workflow ID = creation key":"retry ⟲ 拿回同一条记录——workflow ID = 创建 key","any microservice":"任意微服务","SDK · 1 import":"SDK · 1 个 import","new request type = self-service form · 2 minutes":"新请求类型 = 自助表单 · 2 分钟","OMNI · ERC-20 · TRC-20":"OMNI · ERC-20 · TRC-20","Distributed Systems":"分布式系统","Hybrid apps":"混合应用","the pipeline":"pipeline","Ten stages, one":"十个阶段,一次","gate at a time":"只过一道门","A one-line feature request walks through ten stages, each invoked as":"一句话的功能需求,要走完十个阶段,每个阶段以",". There is no":"调用。没有","— every stage derives its state from the presence and content hash of the artifact the previous stage wrote, and refuses to run until that artifact exists and is approved.":"——每个阶段的状态,都由上一阶段写下的那份产物的存在与内容哈希推导出来;那份产物不存在、没批准,这个阶段就拒绝运行。","1 · Init":"1 · Init","— open the feature workspace; downstream stages populate it, nothing else.":"——开出功能的工作目录;后续阶段往里填,别的什么都不做。","2 · PRD":"2 · PRD","— draft the requirements document, marking every unknown as":"——起草需求文档,把每一处未知都标成","instead of guessing.":",而不是去猜。","3 · Proposal":"3 · Proposal","— frontend/backend design, the API contracts, and the data contract.":"——前后端设计、API 契约,以及数据契约。","4 · Approve":"4 · Approve","— a human sign-off gate on the design. Nothing proceeds without it.":"——设计的人工签核门禁。不过这道门,什么都不往下走。","5 · Proto":"5 · Proto","— generate the":"——生成","contracts and publish the shared gRPC types.":"契约,发布共享的 gRPC 类型。","6 · SDK":"6 · SDK","— update the SDK to consume the freshly-published contracts.":"——更新 SDK,去消费刚发布的契约。","7 · Figma":"7 · Figma","— map the frontend design to components (optional, when there's UI).":"——把前端设计映射到组件(可选,有 UI 时才做)。","8 · Tasks":"8 · Tasks","— a dependency-ordered work breakdown the agents can pick up.":"——一份按依赖排序的任务拆解,供 agent 领取。","9 · Dev":"9 · Dev","— parallel implementation by subagents, one task at a time.":"——subagent 并行实现,一次一个任务。","10 · Verify":"10 · Verify","— machine-judged acceptance against the contracts.":"——对照契约,机器判定验收。","Artifact-gated, human-approved, contract-first. Contracts are generated and shared":"以产物为门禁、人工批准、契约先行。契约的生成与共享,发生在写下","before":"第一行代码之前","a line of code is written — so producers and consumers can't drift.":"——所以生产者和消费者想漂移也漂移不了。","sample: a skill":"样本:一个 skill","A skill is a":"skill 是一份","checklist with teeth":"带牙的清单","Each stage — and each reusable building block — is a skill: a Markdown file the agent reads before it acts. This is a real excerpt from":"每个阶段——以及每个可复用的构件——都是一个 skill:一份 agent 动手之前先读的 Markdown 文件。下面是",", the policy every backend service must satisfy before it's called production-ready. It came out of a real incident.":"的真实节选,这份策略是每个后端服务被称为「可上生产」之前必须满足的。它是从一次真实事故里长出来的。","Real excerpt from the ai-native-sdlc repo — desensitized (neutral service names, no company internals).":"取自 ai-native-sdlc 仓的真实节选——已脱敏(中性的服务名,无公司内部信息)。","The skill also ships stack-specific templates (Rust, NestJS, Node, Java), the K8s manifest, a local SIGTERM test, and a list of anti-patterns to reject in review. Twenty-three skills like this live in the repo — the ten pipeline stages plus reusable blocks.":"这个 skill 还附带各技术栈的模板(Rust、NestJS、Node、Java)、K8s manifest、一份本地 SIGTERM 测试,以及一串 review 时该驳回的反模式。仓里有二十三个这样的 skill——十个 pipeline 阶段,加上可复用的构件。","sample: an agent":"样本:一个 agent","Each reviewer is a":"每个 reviewer 都是","specialist, not a generalist":"专科,而不是全科","The pipeline dispatches role-specialized subagents, each with a tight remit and its own tool budget. Here is the real remit of":"pipeline 派出的是按角色专精的 subagent,每个都有收紧的职责和自己的工具预算。下面是","— one of twelve.":"的真实职责——十二个之一。","Real excerpt from the ai-native-sdlc repo — the agent's own definition file.":"取自 ai-native-sdlc 仓的真实节选——这个 agent 自己的定义文件。","The full roster is twelve:":"完整阵容是十二个:","and":"、",". Each one draws a boundary; none of them can approve its own work.":"。每一个都划出一道边界;没有谁能批准自己的活。","governance":"治理","The discipline the agents":"agent 所遵循的","run under":"纪律","All of it operates under one standing rule set — a desensitized set of Karpathy-derived guidelines that bias toward caution over speed.":"这一切都跑在同一套长期规则下——一份脱敏的、源自 Karpathy 的准则,宁可慢一点,也偏向谨慎。","Human-in-the-loop, always.":"人始终在环内。","Approval gates sit at design and before any publish; the AI never commits or publishes on its own.":"批准门禁设在设计处、以及任何 publish 之前;AI 从不自己 commit 或发布。","Content-hash state.":"以内容哈希为状态。","State lives in the artifacts, not a database. Re-running a stage hashes the upstream artifact and detects changes, so edits ripple forward deterministically.":"状态活在产物里,不在数据库里。重跑一个阶段会对上游产物做哈希、检出改动,所以修改会确定性地向前传导。","No unreviewed merge.":"未经 review 不许 merge。","Every stage produces a reviewable artifact; the next stage refuses to run until the previous one exists and is signed off. Plausible is not correct — nothing merges on hope.":"每个阶段都产出一份可 review 的产物;上一份不存在、没签核,下一阶段就拒绝运行。像样不等于正确——没有东西靠侥幸 merge。","The full":"完整的","build":"构建","The whole pipeline — 10 stages, 23 skills, 12 agents — lives on GitHub, desensitized and MIT-licensed. What you've seen here is a few samples; the rest is in the open.":"整条 pipeline——10 个阶段、23 个 skills、12 个 agents——都在 GitHub 上,已脱敏,MIT 许可。这里看到的只是几个样本,其余的都是公开的。","explore the build on GitHub →":"上 GitHub 看这套构建 →","23 skills · 12 agents":"23 个 skills · 12 个 agents","Backend Engineer & Technical Lead":"后端工程师 & Technical Lead","I design and build distributed backend systems for high-concurrency transaction platforms":"我为高并发交易平台设计和构建分布式后端系统","millions of operations":"数百万次操作","every day.":",每天如此。","Eight years in software, from legacy systems and production scaling to microservices, workflow orchestration, and technical leadership.":"八年软件经验,从 legacy 系统和生产扩容,到微服务、workflow 编排和技术带队。","daily active users":"日活用户","financial operations":"资金操作","SDK releases":"SDK 发布","View selected work":"查看精选案例","Download résumé":"下载简历","request → workflow → execution → ledger":"请求 → workflow → 执行 → 账本","client request":"客户端请求","◆ workflow":"◆ workflow","service execution":"服务执行","Transaction Backbone":"交易主干","Rebuilt a legacy transaction flow into a durable workflow service with safe retries and self-service integration.":"把一条 legacy 交易流程重建成 durable workflow 服务:retry 安全,接入自助。","100+ SDK releases":"100+ 次 SDK 发布","30–60 min → ~2 min onboarding":"接入 30–60 分钟 → ~2 分钟","Explore the case →":"查看案例 →","Scaling the Platform":"平台扩容","Improved core platform mechanisms as daily active users grew from 50k to 400k+.":"在日活从 50k 涨到 400k+ 的过程中,持续改造平台核心机制。","50k → 400k+ DAU":"50k → 400k+ DAU","zero-downtime migration":"零停机迁移","Redis fan-out and routing":"Redis fan-out 与路由","Data Ingestion Pipeline":"数据接入 pipeline","Unified 10M+ daily records from 10+ sources into a reconciled queryable layer.":"把 10+ 个来源、每天 10M+ 条记录,统一进一层对过账、可查询的数据层。","10M+ records/day":"每天 10M+ 条记录","10+ sources":"10+ 个来源","streaming + durable workflows":"流处理 + durable workflow","All case studies →":"全部案例 →","I started in frontend and mobile development, then moved into backend systems, distributed workflows, platform engineering, and technical leadership. Today I lead a four-engineer core backend team across six module domains while staying hands-on with architecture and production systems.":"我从前端和移动端起步,后来转向后端系统、分布式 workflow、平台工程和技术带队。现在我带一个四人核心后端团队,横跨六个模块域,同时仍亲手做架构和生产系统。","Based in Malaysia (UTC+8). Comfortable collaborating across teams through clear documentation and async communication.":"常驻马来西亚(UTC+8)。习惯用清晰的文档和异步沟通做跨团队协作。","View my background →":"查看我的经历 →","Apache Pulsar":"Apache Pulsar","Apache Flink":"Apache Flink","GitHub Actions":"GitHub Actions","Design for the next change":"为下一次变化而设计","I prefer systems that make the next requirement cheaper, not just the current delivery possible.":"我偏好让下一个需求变便宜的系统,而不只是把当前这次交付做出来。","Decide with evidence":"用证据做决定","Important technical decisions should be backed by measurements, prototypes, or production data.":"重要的技术决定,应该有测量、原型或生产数据背书。","Build for recovery":"从一开始就考虑恢复路径","Critical changes should include failure handling, rollback paths, and operational visibility.":"关键改动应该自带失败处理、回滚路径和可观测性。","Write context down":"把上下文写下来","Decisions and trade-offs should be accessible to the team, not stored only in someone's head.":"决策和取舍应该让团队随时能查到,而不是只存在某个人的脑子里。","Based in Malaysia and open to conversations with teams building backend platforms, distributed systems, and developer tooling.":"常驻马来西亚,欢迎在做后端平台、分布式系统和开发者工具的团队来聊。","Always happy to connect with engineers building in this space.":"也随时欢迎同领域的工程师交流。","Résumé (PDF)":"简历(PDF)","Alor Setar, Malaysia · UTC+8":"马来西亚 亚罗士打 · UTC+8","workflow — zsh":"workflow — zsh","$ workflow run <feature>":"$ workflow run <feature>","prd ✓  proposal ✓  contracts ✓  sdk ✓":"prd ✓  proposal ✓  contracts ✓  sdk ✓","tasks → dev → verify":"任务 → 开发 → 验证","⏸ gate: waiting for human approval…":"⏸ gate:等待人工批准…","# AI never commits":"# AI 从不 commit","Staged, artifact-gated development lifecycle":"分阶段、以产物为门禁的开发生命周期","[chat] @bugdoctor error spike, workflow svc":"[chat] @bugdoctor 报错激增,workflow 服务","→ tracing across repos… (MCP: logs + code)":"→ 跨 repo 追踪中…(MCP:日志 + 代码)","→ hypothesis: stale credential cache":"→ 假设:过期的凭证缓存","→ evidence: trace id 8f3a · 3 log lines":"→ 证据:trace id 8f3a · 3 行日志","# hours of triage → minutes":"# 数小时排查 → 几分钟","Bug Doctor":"Bug Doctor","Chat Bot":"Chat Bot","schema — zsh":"schema — zsh","$ schema build events/*.json":"$ schema build events/*.json","codegen → node ✓  java ✓  rust ✓":"codegen → node ✓  java ✓  rust ✓","publish → sdk v1.0.34":"publish → sdk v1.0.34","# producers and consumers can't drift":"# 生产者和消费者想漂移也漂移不了","JSON Schema":"JSON Schema","[chat] @reach send a $10 bonus to users registered on Jan 12":"[chat] @reach 给 1 月 12 日注册的用户发 $10 奖励","→ target preview ready · audit logged":"→ 目标名单预览就绪 · 审计已记录","⏸ waiting for \"confirm\"…":"⏸ 等待输入 \"confirm\"…","→ executed · results reported to chat ✓":"→ 已执行 · 结果已回报到 chat ✓","# preview first · a human confirms · audit always":"# 先预览 · 人来确认 · 审计常在","Zod Tools":"Zod Tools","context — zsh":"context — zsh","$ agent task \"add a field to the contract\"":"$ agent task \"给契约加一个字段\"","→ repo resolved (1 of 17) · context loaded":"→ repo 已定位(17 选 1)· context 已加载","→ memory: prior decisions recalled":"→ memory:召回了过往决策","# the prompt is engineered context, not clever words":"# prompt 是工程化的 context,不是花哨的措辞","[to confirm]":"[to confirm]","Live demos":"在线 demo","Interactive rebuilds of designs from the case studies — try them in the browser.":"把案例里的设计做成可交互的重现——在浏览器里直接试。","Run the demo →":"运行 demo →","This site's own repository activity, streamed straight from the GitHub API.":"本站自己的仓库动态,直接从 GitHub API 拉取。","hermes — zsh":"hermes — zsh","$ hermes take \"update the portfolio\"":"$ hermes take \"更新 portfolio\"","plan → edit → self-check → report":"计划 → 修改 → 自检 → 汇报","⏸ gate: human review before deploy":"⏸ gate:部署前人工 review","# it maintains this very site":"# 它维护的就是这个网站","Nous Hermes":"Nous Hermes","Telegram + WhatsApp":"Telegram + WhatsApp","pandas + ta":"pandas + ta","Moomoo OpenD":"Moomoo OpenD","Claude Code Skill":"Claude Code Skill","OpenAI API":"OpenAI API","Streamlit · Zeabur":"Streamlit · Zeabur","UM890 · WSL2":"UM890 · WSL2","Vanilla JS":"Vanilla JS","Deep-dive: Hermes, an LLM-in-the-loop trading research system":"深入:Hermes,一个 LLM-in-the-loop 的交易研究系统","A personal side project — three repos, news → signals → offline validation, with the model kept on a tight leash: it narrates the numbers, deterministic code computes them. The honest problem-and-solution log, gaps included, lives on":"一个个人 side project——三个 repo,news → signals → 离线验证,模型被拴得很紧:数字由确定性代码来算,它只负责叙述。诚实的问题与解法记录(包括没补上的坑)都在","the Hermes page":"Hermes 页面","json_repair.py — illustrative":"json_repair.py — 示意代码","route_content.py — illustrative":"route_content.py — 示意代码","stage0_self_check.py — illustrative":"stage0_self_check.py — 示意代码","github.com/henrylee94/hermes-news ↗":"github.com/henrylee94/hermes-news ↗","github.com/henrylee94/hermes-trading ↗":"github.com/henrylee94/hermes-trading ↗","github.com/henrylee94/hermes-backtest ↗":"github.com/henrylee94/hermes-backtest ↗","selected work":"精选案例","Eight case studies covering transaction workflows, platform scaling, data ingestion, support systems, reporting, payments, and delivery tooling. The three most important come first.":"八个案例,覆盖交易 workflow、平台扩容、数据接入、客服系统、报表、支付和交付工具链。最重要的三个排在最前。","Case 01 · featured":"案例 01 · 精选","Every financial transaction passes one audited approval workflow — millions a day. I rebuilt it on gRPC + Temporal with idempotency by construction, so a retry can only return the record it already made, and turned integration into a published SDK: adding a new request type is a two-minute self-service form.":"每一笔资金交易都走同一条经审计的审批 workflow——每天数百万笔。我用 gRPC + Temporal 重建了它,幂等 by construction,retry 只可能拿回它已经创建的那条记录;接入做成对外发布的 SDK:新增一种请求类型是一张两分钟的自助表单。","Case 02 · featured":"案例 02 · 精选","As the platform grew, ID generation, notification fan-out and blocking scans each hit the old architecture's limits. I measured where the time actually went, then replaced each mechanism in production — no downtime, users online, every step revertible.":"随着平台增长,ID 生成、通知 fan-out、阻塞式扫描接连撞上老架构的上限。我先量清楚时间到底花在哪,再在生产上逐个替换这些机制——零停机,用户在线,每一步都可 revert。","Case 03 · featured":"案例 03 · 精选","Every balance change a user sees, pulled from 10+ heterogeneous systems — most of which my team didn't own — aligned record by record into one reconciled, queryable layer that downstream analytics builds on.":"用户看到的每一次余额变动,来自 10+ 个异构系统——大多不归我的团队管——逐条对齐进一层对过账、可查询的数据层,下游分析都建在它上面。","Case 04 — Support System":"案例 04 — 客服系统","the platform needed a real-time support channel and had none.":"平台需要一个实时客服渠道,当时一片空白。","My part:":"我的部分:","built it from zero on a stack new to the company — AI-assisted handling with human takeover.":"在公司没人用过的技术栈上从零搭起来——AI 辅助处理,人可随时接管。","grew it to a team and handed it off; they run it independently.":"把它养成一个团队后干净交接,现在他们独立运营。","Case 05 — Reporting Engine":"案例 05 — 报表引擎","the business needed analytics and compliance reporting before a dedicated BI team existed.":"在还没有专职 BI 团队的时候,业务就需要分析和合规报表。","built and ran the reporting engine for six years — multi-view analytics over million-row datasets.":"搭建并运营这套报表引擎六年——在百万行级数据集上做多视角分析。","140+ reporting changes, regulatory filings delivered on time.":"140+ 次报表变更,监管报送按时交付。","Case 06 — AI Delivery Pipeline":"案例 06 — AI 交付 pipeline","a small team, a growing backlog, and AI tools that produce plausible-but-wrong output when unmanaged.":"小团队、不断增长的 backlog,以及一放任就产出“看着对、其实错”结果的 AI 工具。","a staged delivery pipeline where AI drafts and humans gate every merge.":"一条分阶段的交付 pipeline:AI 起草,每次 merge 由人把关。","16 features shipped through it; first drafts in hours instead of days.":"16 个 feature 经它交付;初稿从几天缩到几小时。","Case 07 — Multi-Currency & Crypto Integration":"案例 07 — 多币种 & 加密货币集成","the platform needed crypto payment paths where a precision slip is real loss.":"平台需要加密货币支付通道,而这里精度一滑就是真实损失。","deposits, withdrawals and transfers threaded through every transaction boundary, with provider integration and reconciliation.":"把充值、提现、转账穿过每一个交易边界,连同供应商对接和对账。","two years in production across three wallet protocols.":"横跨三种钱包协议,在生产环境跑了两年。","Case 08 — Cross-Stack Rewards Pipeline":"案例 08 — 跨栈奖励 pipeline","a rewards path across four services in three languages, where a double-pay is real loss.":"一条横跨四个服务、三种语言的奖励链路,重复发放就是真实损失。","designed the exactly-once layer — an atomic claims ledger plus a human-readable idempotency key.":"设计了 exactly-once 层——一张原子化的领取台账,加一个人类可读的幂等 key。","correct under workflow replays and message redeliveries, with zero changes to legacy services.":"在 workflow replay 和消息重投下依然正确,legacy 服务零改动。","Platform overview":"平台全景","How the case studies connect — a transaction record flows through these systems end to end.":"这些案例如何串起来——一条交易记录端到端流经这些系统。","Some of these systems I built, some I run, some my team owns — the point is that they have to add up end to end.":"这些系统有的是我建的,有的由我运营,有的归我团队——关键是它们端到端必须对得上。","Hitachi Ebworx":"Hitachi Ebworx","case 01 / 08":"案例 01 / 08","Module owner — designed the service, led the migration, run it in production today.":"模块 owner——设计了这个服务,主导迁移,今天仍在生产上运行它。","Millions of transactions a day, peaks around a thousand per second; 200+ request types on one base workflow.":"每天数百万笔交易,峰值约每秒一千笔;200+ 种请求类型跑在一条 base workflow 上。","NestJS · gRPC · Temporal · MongoDB · published SDK with semantic versioning.":"NestJS · gRPC · Temporal · MongoDB · 对外发布的 SDK,遵循语义化版本。","Duplicate execution prevented by construction; new-type onboarding cut from 30–60 minutes to ~2; 100+ SDK releases.":"重复执行由构造杜绝;新类型接入从 30–60 分钟压到约 2 分钟;100+ 次 SDK 发布。","Every financial transaction on the platform — withdrawal, top-up, loyalty reward, configuration change — must pass one audited create → review → approve → execute lifecycle. The legacy implementation was tightly coupled inside a monolith: every consumer re-implemented its own wiring, retries lived in cron-driven scanners, and adding a new request type was a 30-to-60-minute, person-dependent process that queued on the core team.":"平台上每一笔金融交易——提现、充值、忠诚奖励、配置变更——都必须走同一条带审计的 create → review → approve → execute 生命周期。旧实现和单体紧紧耦在一起:每个接入方都要自己重新实现一遍接线,重试靠 cron 驱动的扫描器,新增一种请求类型是一个 30–60 分钟、依赖特定人的流程,还要排核心团队的队。","Traffic growth made this untenable — the flow was heading past what the old architecture could hold, and any duplicate execution on this path means a transaction is processed twice.":"流量增长让这一切难以为继——流量正在越过旧架构能承受的上限,而这条路径上任何一次重复执行,都意味着一笔交易被处理了两次。","Production traffic could not stop: the platform's single point of trust, live throughout the migration.":"生产流量不能停:这是平台唯一的信任锚点,整个迁移期间都在线。","Financial correctness — a retried create must never produce a second record.":"资金正确性——被 retry 的 create 绝不能产生第二条记录。","Backward compatibility — legacy consumers stayed on the old endpoints until each flow cut over, with endpoint-level fallback.":"向后兼容——旧接入方停留在旧 endpoint 上,直到各自的流程完成切流,并带 endpoint 级降级回退。","Auditability — every state transition reviewed, logged, and traceable.":"可审计——每一次状态迁移都经过审核、留有日志、可以追溯。","Cross-team integration — downstream services on different schedules had to adopt at their own pace.":"跨团队集成——下游服务节奏各不相同,必须能按自己的步调接入。","I own this module. I designed the service, wrote the initial production version, planned the migration path from the monolith, and coordinated the gRPC contracts consuming teams integrate against. The SDK and its release discipline are mine; the request-type patterns other services copy started here. Implementation beyond the initial version was shared with my team.":"这个模块归我 own。我设计了这个服务,写下第一个生产版本,规划了从单体迁出的路径,并协调各接入团队所依赖的 gRPC 契约。SDK 及其发版纪律出自我手;其他服务照抄的请求类型模式也是从这里开始的。初始版本之后的实现由我和团队共同完成。","A gRPC microservice orchestrated by Temporal: one generic durable workflow runs every request type, with business extension points as child-workflow slots. Idempotency is structural — the workflow ID doubles as the creation key, so a retried step returns the existing record instead of creating twice. Integration is a published SDK: any service registers an executor with one import.":"一个由 Temporal 编排的 gRPC 微服务:一条通用的持久化 workflow 跑所有请求类型,业务扩展点做成 child-workflow 插槽。幂等是结构性的——workflow ID 兼任创建 key,所以被 retry 的步骤只会拿回已存在的记录,而不是创建第二条。接入就是一个对外发布的 SDK:任何服务一个 import 就能注册 executor。","create → review → approve → execute, one audited path for every transaction type. Human review sits in the middle; the engine owns retries and timeouts.":"create → review → approve → execute,所有交易类型走同一条带审计的路径。人工审核居中;重试和超时归引擎管。","Walkthrough — what each state does":"逐步拆解——每个状态在做什么","First request:":"第一次请求:","the workflow ID is derived from the request, the record is created, the lifecycle starts.":"workflow ID 由请求推导得出,记录被创建,生命周期开始。","the same derivation finds the existing record and returns it — no second write.":"同样的推导找到已存在的记录并把它返回——不会有第二次写入。","Worker failure:":"worker 故障:","the engine replays the workflow history on another worker; completed steps are not re-executed.":"引擎在另一台 worker 上重放 workflow 历史;已完成的步骤不会被重复执行。","Existing record return:":"返回已存在记录:","the caller receives the same transaction ID either way.":"无论哪种情况,调用方拿到的都是同一个交易 ID。","human review":"人工审核","Durable workflows over cron-and-scan":"持久化 workflow,而不是 cron 加扫描","Keep the legacy pattern — cron jobs re-scanning for stuck approvals — or move orchestration into a durable workflow engine.":"沿用旧模式——用 cron 任务反复扫描卡住的审批——还是把编排搬进持久化 workflow 引擎。","Temporal. Retries, timeouts and recovery belong in the engine, not in scanners.":"选 Temporal。重试、超时和恢复应该属于引擎,而不是扫描器。","I had personally operated the 22-cron-job version for years; the failure modes were known and structural.":"那个 22 个 cron 任务的版本我亲手运维了多年;失败模式众所周知,而且是结构性的。","A new operational surface: worker fleets, task queues, and replay-deterministic code discipline the team had to learn.":"一整块新的运维面:worker 集群、task queue,以及团队必须学会的 replay 确定性代码纪律。","One generic workflow, not one per request type":"一条通用 workflow,而不是每种请求类型一条","A workflow implementation per transaction type, or one base workflow with business extension slots.":"每种交易类型各写一个 workflow 实现,还是一条 base workflow 加业务扩展插槽。","One base workflow; 200+ request types run through it.":"一条 base workflow;200+ 种请求类型都从它上面跑。","Every new type inherits idempotency, audit and retry behaviour for free — correctness is written once.":"每个新类型免费继承幂等、审计和重试行为——正确性只写一次。","The base workflow is high-blast-radius code: changes ship behind version markers and get the strictest review on the team.":"base workflow 是高爆炸半径的代码:改动都藏在版本标记后面发布,并接受团队里最严格的 review。","Cutover carried by the SDK, with endpoint-level fallback":"切流由 SDK 承载,带 endpoint 级降级回退","Big-bang switch, or migrate flow by flow with the SDK routing between old and new endpoints.":"big-bang 一次性切换,还是逐条流程迁移,由 SDK 在新旧 endpoint 之间路由。","Framework first, then flow-by-flow cutover; every endpoint could fall back independently.":"框架先行,然后逐条流程切流;每个 endpoint 都能独立回退。","On a live financial path, each step needs its own rollback — a big-bang cutover has none.":"在一条线上资金路径上,每一步都需要自己的回退——big-bang 切流什么回退都没有。","Two systems ran in parallel during the migration window, which meant double observability and double support until retirement.":"迁移窗口内两套系统并行,意味着双份的可观测和双份的支持,直到旧系统退役。","Real incidents and the mechanisms that came out of them.":"真实的事故,以及从中长出来的机制。","Customer support found it before any dashboard did: a reward-redemption flow was handing out value without deducting the balance. A pre-charge step in the workflow was being skipped — silently. Rollback first, debug second. The trail led to a shared contract file that had quietly fallen behind on one branch; a routine package upgrade activated the stale copy.":"最先发现的是客服,不是任何一块 dashboard:一条奖励兑换流程在发放价值,却没有扣减余额。workflow 里的预扣费步骤被跳过了——而且是静默跳过。先回退,再排查。线索指向一份共享契约文件,它在某个分支上悄悄落后了;一次例行的包升级把这份过期副本激活了。","The fixes were systemic, not local: the workflow fails loudly if the pre-charge step doesn't run; every release regression-tests every transaction path; and the incident seeded the first version of our risk-alerting pipeline — every redemption event published onto the event bus, alerting the risk team in chat.":"修复是系统性的,不是局部的:预扣费步骤没跑,workflow 就大声失败;每次发版都对所有交易路径做回归测试;这次事故还催生了我们风控告警 pipeline 的第一个版本——每个兑换事件都发布到事件总线上,在群聊里提醒风控团队。","A third-party callback landed before our own state had finished persisting — the workflow received a signal for a record that, from its point of view, didn't exist yet. The fix was structural: signals are buffered until the state they refer to has landed, and every behavioural change ships behind a versioned patch marker, so workflows already running mid-history replay the exact logic they started with. In durable workflows, a code deploy is an event your running history has to survive.":"一个第三方回调比我们自己的状态落库更早到达——workflow 收到了一个信号,而它所指的记录,在 workflow 看来还不存在。修复是结构性的:信号会被缓冲,直到它所指的状态落地;每一次行为变更都藏在带版本的 patch 标记后面发布,让已经跑到历史中途的 workflow 重放它们启动时的那套逻辑。在持久化 workflow 里,一次代码部署,就是一个你正在运行的历史必须挺过去的事件。","The engine retries failed steps — that's the point of it. But on a transaction path, a retried create is a potential duplicate record. So creation isn't guarded by a check bolted on afterwards; it's guarded by construction: the workflow ID doubles as the record's creation key, and every create looks up before it writes. Updates carry status guards, and illegal state transitions throw instead of writing.":"引擎会重试失败的步骤——这正是它存在的意义。但在交易路径上,一次被 retry 的 create 就是一条潜在的重复记录。所以创建不是靠事后补一个检查来守护,而是由构造守护:workflow ID 兼任记录的创建 key,每次 create 都先查再写。更新带状态守卫,非法的状态迁移直接抛错而不是写入。","Several environments shared one workflow-engine cluster, and workers began stealing each other's tasks. The fix was a naming discipline, not more hardware: task-queue names resolve per environment — production fixed, local runs suffixed with the developer's identity, test lanes with the environment. Shared infrastructure needs namespacing before it needs capacity.":"几个环境共用一个 workflow 引擎集群,worker 开始互相偷任务。修复靠的是命名纪律,不是加机器:task queue 名称按环境解析——生产固定,本地跑加开发者身份后缀,测试通道带环境后缀。共享基础设施先需要 namespacing,然后才需要容量。","Representative code":"代表性代码","Rewritten for publication to show the production design — not company source.":"为公开发布重写,用来展示生产设计——不是公司源码。","Integration tests run against real dependencies via Testcontainers, not mocks. The test that matters most on this path: fire the same create twice, assert one record exists and both responses carry the same transaction ID.":"集成测试通过 Testcontainers 跑真实依赖,而不是 mock。这条路径上最重要的那个测试:同一个 create 发两次,断言只存在一条记录,且两个响应带的是同一个交易 ID。","Temporal brought real operational complexity — worker fleets, task-queue management, and a replay-determinism discipline every contributor has to learn before touching workflow code.":"Temporal 带来了实打实的运维复杂度——worker 集群、task queue 管理,以及每个贡献者动 workflow 代码之前都必须学会的 replay 确定性纪律。","During migration, the legacy path and the new service ran in parallel: duplicated infrastructure, double monitoring, and a longer tail of support until the old flows retired.":"迁移期间,旧路径和新服务并行:重复的基础设施、双份的监控,以及一条更长的支持尾巴,直到旧流程退役。","The generic base workflow concentrates risk: a defect there touches every request type, which is why changes to it move slower than anywhere else in the module.":"通用 base workflow 把风险集中到了一处:那里的一个缺陷会波及所有请求类型,所以对它的改动比模块里任何地方都走得慢。","Millions of transactions a day in production, still climbing.":"生产环境每天数百万笔交易,还在往上爬。","Duplicate execution prevented by construction rather than caught after the fact.":"重复执行由构造杜绝,而不是事后捕获。","New-type integration went from a 30–60-minute, person-dependent process to ~2-minute self-service.":"新类型接入从一个 30–60 分钟、依赖特定人的流程,变成约 2 分钟的自助服务。","100+ SDK releases under semantic versioning; 200+ request types on one base workflow.":"100+ 次 SDK 发布,遵循语义化版本;200+ 种请求类型跑在一条 base workflow 上。","The SDK-per-domain pattern became the template later platform services copied.":"每个领域一个 SDK 的模式,成了后来平台服务照抄的模板。","On a financial path, idempotency can't be a best effort bolted on afterwards — it has to be impossible to get wrong, which means it lives in the data model, not in a check. And durable workflows change what a deploy is: code changes become events your running histories have to survive, so versioning discipline matters as much as the business logic. Finally, the highest-leverage thing I built here wasn't the service — it was the self-service integration path that took the core team out of every consumer's critical path.":"在资金路径上,幂等不能是事后补上的尽力而为——它必须不可能做错,这意味着它得住在数据模型里,而不是一个检查里。持久化 workflow 还改变了「部署」的含义:代码变更成了你正在运行的历史必须挺过去的事件,所以版本纪律和业务逻辑同样重要。最后,我在这里做的杠杆最高的东西不是这个服务本身——而是那条自助接入路径,它把核心团队从每个接入方的关键路径上摘了出来。","Next: Scaling the Platform →":"下一篇:平台扩容 →","case 02 / 08":"案例 02 / 08","Scaling the":"扩容 ","Drove the scaling work as the platform grew — measured the bottlenecks, designed the replacements, and landed them with the team inside the weekly release train.":"随着平台增长,我驱动了这轮扩容——量出瓶颈、设计替代方案,并和团队一起把它们塞进每周发版的节奏里落地。","50k → 400k+ daily active users over four years; every change shipped live, with users on.":"四年里日活从 50k → 400k+;每个改动都是线上发布,用户全程在线。","Redis (INCR · Pub/Sub · SSCAN) · MongoDB · WebSocket gateway · TypeScript services.":"Redis(INCR · Pub/Sub · SSCAN)· MongoDB · WebSocket 网关 · TypeScript 服务。","Old failure modes gone at 400k+ DAU; sub-second pushes; 30-day report queries where one day used to time out; every cutover zero-downtime and revertible.":"400k+ 日活下旧的失败模式不再出现;亚秒级推送;过去查一天都超时的报表,如今能查 30 天;每次切流都零停机、可回退。","Over four years the member management platform grew from 50k to 400k+ daily active users, and growth kept finding the limits of the old mechanisms. A counter document in the database serialized every ID issued. Notification fan-out ran from one process to every connection and stalled under load. Blocking full-set scans held Redis while they ran. An in-memory config cache grew without bound and leaked. Report queries on the busiest collection couldn't return a single day's records without timing out.":"四年里,会员管理平台的日活从 50k 涨到 400k+,增长不断把旧机制的极限找出来。数据库里的一份 counter 文档把每个 ID 的发放都串行化。通知 fan-out 从一个进程推到所有连接,高负载下卡死。阻塞式的全量扫描一跑起来就占住 Redis。一个内存配置缓存无限增长、还在泄漏。最忙的那个 collection 上,报表查询连一天的记录都取不回来,直接超时。","More than once, the failure happened in production first. Each of these was a live global single-point — the question was never just what to replace it with, but how to replace it with users online.":"不止一次,故障是先在生产上发生的。这里每一个都是线上的全局单点——问题从来不只是用什么替换它,而是怎么在用户在线的情况下替换它。","No downtime allowance — the platform stayed live through every change, users on.":"没有停机额度——每次改动平台都保持在线,用户在线。","No rewrite budget — every fix had to land inside the weekly release train, alongside normal feature work.":"没有重写预算——每个修复都得塞进每周发版的节奏,和日常功能开发并行。","Every target was a live global single-point, so each step needed its own rollback before it shipped.":"每个改造对象都是线上全局单点,所以每一步在发布之前就得有自己的回退。","ID generation could never produce a collision — old and new generators had to be safe to run at the same time.":"ID 生成绝不能产生碰撞——新旧生成器必须能安全地同时运行。","I drove this work as the platform grew: I championed bringing a distributed cache into the platform, measured where the time actually went before proposing changes, root-caused each bottleneck to its mechanism, and designed the replacements and their cutover plans. Implementation and delivery were shared with the team — the changes shipped through the same weekly release train as everything else.":"这项工作是我随平台增长一路推动的:我提案把分布式缓存引入平台,在提出改动之前先量清楚时间到底花在哪,把每个瓶颈都追到它的机制层面,并设计了替代方案和各自的切流计划。实现和交付由团队共同完成——这些改动和其他所有东西一样,走的是同一条每周发版的节奏。","The principle was to replace the mechanism, not the symptom. ID generation moved from a database counter document to atomic Redis INCR. Notification fan-out moved to Redis Pub/Sub: publish once per event, and channel names route each user's events so an instance only touches the sockets it actually holds. Blocking SMEMBERS scans became cursor-based SSCAN. The leaking in-memory config cache was rebuilt cache-aside — read local, fall through to Redis, refresh on a fixed 15-minute cycle. Underneath it all, the query layer was retuned: covering indexes matched to real query shapes, unused indexes removed, aggregation pipelines rebuilt, text search moved off regex scans onto a proper search index.":"原则是换掉机制,而不是治症状。ID 生成从数据库 counter 文档迁到原子的 Redis INCR。通知 fan-out 迁到 Redis Pub/Sub:每个事件只发布一次,channel 名称路由每个用户的事件,一个实例只碰它实际持有的 socket。阻塞式的 SMEMBERS 扫描换成基于 cursor 的 SSCAN。泄漏的内存配置缓存按 cache-aside 重建——先读本地,落空再读 Redis,固定 15 分钟刷新一轮。在这一切之下,查询层也重新调过:covering index 对准真实的查询形状,删掉没人用的索引,aggregation pipeline 逐段重建,文本搜索从 regex 扫描迁到真正的搜索索引上。","Before → after":"之前 → 之后","Database counter → Redis INCR with a +1-billion offset. Single-process WebSocket fan-out → Pub/Sub across N instances. Blocking SMEMBERS → SSCAN cursors. Unbounded in-memory cache → bounded cache-aside with a fixed refresh cycle.":"数据库 counter → Redis INCR,带 +10 亿偏移。单进程 WebSocket fan-out → 跨 N 个实例的 Pub/Sub。阻塞式 SMEMBERS → SSCAN 游标。无上限的内存缓存 → 有界的 cache-aside,固定周期刷新。","Walkthrough — how a live cutover ran":"逐步拆解——一次线上切流是怎么跑的","the new mechanism starts in a range or path that cannot collide with the old one — for IDs, one billion above the old counter.":"新机制从一个不可能与旧机制相撞的区间或路径起步——对 ID 来说,就是旧 counter 之上 10 亿的位置。","Run both:":"两边同跑:","old and new operate at the same time; neither can corrupt the other.":"新旧同时运行;谁也不可能弄脏谁。","Cut over:":"切流:","traffic moves in small, individually revertible steps, one release at a time.":"流量以小步迁移,每一步都可独立回退,一次发版走一步。","boring on purpose — point back at the old mechanism. Each step's rollback existed before the step shipped.":"故意做得很无聊——指回旧机制就行。每一步的回退,在这一步发布之前就已经存在。","ID cutover by offset, not choreography":"ID 切流靠偏移,不靠编排","Choreograph a precise handover between two live ID generators, or start the new range one billion above the old counter so both can run at once.":"在两个活着的 ID 生成器之间编排一次精准的交接,还是让新区间从旧 counter 之上 10 亿的位置起步,两边可以同时跑。","The +1-billion offset. Old and new generators ran in parallel and could never collide.":"+10 亿的偏移。新旧生成器并行运行,永远不可能相撞。","With users online and no maintenance window, the safest cutover is the one where collision is impossible by construction, not prevented by timing.":"用户在线、没有维护窗口,最安全的切流,是那个碰撞由构造保证不可能、而不是靠时机防住的方案。","A permanent billion-wide gap in the ID sequence, and ID issuance now depends on Redis being up — a new availability dependency the team had to operate.":"ID 序列里留下一道永久的 10 亿宽的空洞,而且 ID 发放从此依赖 Redis 在线——一个团队必须运维的新可用性依赖。","Move fan-out to Pub/Sub instead of tuning the sockets":"把 fan-out 迁到 Pub/Sub,而不是去调 socket","Tune the WebSocket layer — the visible component — or measure first and change whatever the profile pointed at.":"去调 WebSocket 层——那个看得见的组件——还是先测量,profile 指向哪就改哪。","Measurement showed the cost was the single-process fan-out loop, not the sockets. We published each event once to Redis Pub/Sub; every instance subscribes and delivers only to the connections it holds.":"测量表明,开销在单进程的 fan-out 循环,不在 socket。我们把每个事件只发布一次到 Redis Pub/Sub;每个实例订阅后,只投递给自己持有的连接。","Channel-per-user routing removes the single fan-out point entirely and scales delivery with the number of instances.":"按用户分 channel 的路由彻底移除了那个单一的 fan-out 点,投递能力随实例数量伸缩。","Redis Pub/Sub is fire-and-forget — an instance that is down during publish misses the message — so delivery behaviour under Redis failure had to be understood and accepted for notifications.":"Redis Pub/Sub 是 fire-and-forget——发布时恰好宕机的实例会错过消息——所以 Redis 故障下的投递行为,必须先弄清楚,并确认对通知场景可以接受。","Unit of change = unit of rollback":"变更的单位 = 回退的单位","Ship each migration as one big change, or as a series of small, individually revertible steps.":"每次迁移是当成一个大改动发出去,还是拆成一串小而各自可回退的步骤。","Small steps in series, each with its own rollback. The fan-out migration taught us this the hard way: the first landing shipped as one change, production surprised us, and we reverted the whole thing.":"小步连发,每一步带自己的回退。fan-out 迁移用惨痛的方式教会了我们这一点:第一次落地是当成一个改动发的,生产给了我们意外,我们把整个东西 revert 了。","On a live platform the design being right isn't enough — the delivery has to be revertible at the same granularity it ships.":"在一个线上平台,设计对是不够的——交付必须在它发布的同一粒度上可回退。","Slower delivery: more releases per migration, and a longer window where old and new mechanisms run in parallel and both need watching.":"交付更慢:每次迁移要更多次发版,新旧机制并行、两边都要盯着的窗口也更长。","What broke, and the practices that came out of it.":"什么坏掉了,以及从中长出来的实践。","Reports that stopped coming back":"再也跑不回来的报表","One stretch of growth broke the reporting layer visibly: operational reports stopped returning, and on the busiest collection a query couldn't fetch a single day's records without timing out. Recovery was months of unglamorous work — reading the slow-query log, matching covering indexes to the query shapes people actually ran, deleting the indexes nobody used (on write-heavy collections an unused index is pure tax), rebuilding aggregation pipelines stage by stage, and moving text search off regex scans onto a search index. Thirty-day report windows came back comfortably where one day used to time out.":"有一段增长期把报表层弄坏得肉眼可见:运营报表不再返回,最忙的那个 collection 上,一条查询连一天的记录都取不回来,直接超时。恢复是好几个月不体面的苦活——读慢查询日志,把 covering index 对准大家真正在跑的查询形状,删掉没人用的索引(在写多的 collection 上,一个没人用的索引就是纯税),把 aggregation pipeline 一段一段重建,把文本搜索从 regex 扫描迁到搜索索引上。过去查一天都超时的地方,30 天的报表窗口回来了,而且跑得从容。","Push notifications were arriving late, and the room's instinct was to tune the WebSocket layer — the visible component. Measuring where the time actually went showed the cost was the fan-out loop behind the sockets, delivering to every connection from one place. Fan-out moved to Pub/Sub and pushes went sub-second. The loudest component is rarely the bottleneck; the profile decides.":"推送通知在肉眼可见地迟到,屋里所有人的直觉都是去调 WebSocket 层——那个看得见的组件。量清楚时间到底花在哪之后,发现开销在 socket 背后的 fan-out 循环:所有连接的投递都从一个地方发出。fan-out 迁到 Pub/Sub 之后,推送进了亚秒级。最吵的组件很少是真正的瓶颈;由 profile 说了算。","The fan-out migration shipped — and production surprised us, so we reverted. The second landing was a series of small, individually revertible steps, each hardened by what the first attempt taught us. Nothing about the design was wrong; the delivery was. The rule that came out of it — the unit of change has to equal the unit of rollback — applied to every migration after.":"fan-out 迁移发布了——生产给了我们意外,于是我们 revert。第二次落地是一串小而各自可回退的步骤,每一步都用第一次的教训加固过。设计没有任何问题;错的是交付。从这里长出来的规则——变更的单位必须等于回退的单位——适用于之后的每一次迁移。","The platform-wide practice applied here: Jest with Testcontainers against real databases rather than mocks, an 80% coverage gate, and a full regression pass every week before release — which is what made shipping migrations inside the release train tolerable. Beyond the suite, every mechanism change was validated by measurement: profile before to find the real bottleneck, run old and new in parallel where possible, and watch the same metric after each revertible step before taking the next one.":"这里沿用的是全平台的实践:Jest 配 Testcontainers 跑真实数据库而不是 mock,80% 的覆盖率门禁,每周发版前跑一轮完整回归——正是这些,让在发版节奏里塞迁移这件事变得可以忍受。测试套件之外,每一次机制变更都靠测量验证:改之前先 profile 找到真正的瓶颈,能并行就新旧并行跑,每走完一个可回退的步骤,先盯同一个指标,再走下一步。","Operational complexity: Redis went from a cache to core infrastructure — ID issuance, notification delivery and config reads all depend on it, so its memory, monitoring and failover became things the team had to own.":"运维复杂度:Redis 从一个缓存变成了核心基础设施——ID 发放、通知投递、配置读取都依赖它,它的内存、监控和 failover 从此都是团队必须 own 的东西。","Redis failure behaviour: Pub/Sub is fire-and-forget, so an instance that is down at publish time misses the message — acceptable for notifications, and part of why the audited transaction path never moved onto it. If Redis is unavailable, new ID issuance stops rather than risking a collision.":"Redis 故障行为:Pub/Sub 是 fire-and-forget,发布时宕机的实例会错过消息——对通知可以接受,这也是带审计的交易路径从未迁到它上面的原因之一。Redis 不可用时,新 ID 的发放会直接停下,而不是冒碰撞的风险。","Observability requirements: revertible steps only work if you can see them working — each cutover needed before/after measurement and a watch window, and during migration both old and new mechanisms had to be monitored at once.":"可观测性要求:可回退的步骤,只有在你能看见它们在正常工作时才成立——每次切流都需要前后测量和一个观察窗口,迁移期间新旧机制还得同时监控。","Consistency: the cache-aside config layer trades freshness for boundedness — an edit can take up to the 15-minute refresh cycle to converge across instances, a window that had to be acceptable to the people changing configs.":"一致性:cache-aside 的配置层用新鲜度换有界性——一次修改最多要等一个 15 分钟的刷新周期才能在所有实例间收敛,这个窗口必须让改配置的人能够接受。","Migration in small steps was slower than a big-bang cutover would have been — more releases, and a longer parallel-run tail.":"小步迁移比 big-bang 切流要慢——更多次发版,更长的并行运行尾巴。","The platform sustains 400k+ daily active users without the old failure modes.":"平台稳定支撑 400k+ 日活,旧的失败模式不再出现。","Push notifications went from visibly late to sub-second, delivered across N instances.":"推送通知从肉眼可见的迟到变成亚秒级,跨 N 个实例投递。","Thirty-day report queries return comfortably on collections where a single day used to time out.":"过去查一天都超时的 collection 上,30 天的报表查询如今从容返回。","ID generation cut over live with zero downtime and zero collisions; rollback stayed one config change away throughout.":"ID 生成在线上完成切流,零停机、零碰撞;全程回退始终只差一个配置变更。","The patterns introduced — cache-aside, atomic counters, pub/sub fan-out — became house standards for modules built after.":"这次引入的模式——cache-aside、原子计数、pub/sub fan-out——成了之后新模块的团队标准。","Measure before arguing — the visible component is rarely the bottleneck, and the profile settles debates that intuition keeps open. Replace mechanisms, not symptoms: tuning a serialized counter or a single-process fan-out loop only postpones the same failure. And on a live platform, delivery design matters as much as system design — the +1-billion offset and the reverted-then-relanded fan-out both taught the same lesson: prefer the change with nothing left to go wrong, and make its unit of change equal its unit of rollback.":"先测量,再争论——看得见的组件很少是真正的瓶颈,直觉吵不完的问题,profile 一出来就定了。换掉机制,而不是治症状:去调一个被串行化的 counter 或一个单进程 fan-out 循环,只是把同一场故障往后推。而在一个线上平台,交付设计和系统设计同样重要——+10 亿的偏移,和那次 revert 后重新落地的 fan-out,教的是同一课:优先选那个没有任何东西可以再出错的方案,并让它变更的单位等于回退的单位。","Next: Data Ingestion Pipeline →":"下一篇:数据接入 pipeline →","case 03 / 08":"案例 03 / 08","Data Ingestion":"数据接入","Hand-built the pipeline end to end, drove alignment across the teams that own the sources, and reconciled the historical data myself.":"亲手把这条 pipeline 端到端搭起来,推动各来源 owner 团队对齐方向,历史数据也是我自己逐条对账补齐的。","Over ten million records a day and climbing, from 10+ heterogeneous sources — the platform's most demanding data path.":"每天上千万条记录、仍在增长,来自 10+ 个异构来源——平台上要求最苛刻的数据路径。","Flink stream processing · Temporal durable workflows · Hologres columnar analytics store · operational store with covering indexes.":"Flink 流式处理 · Temporal 持久化 workflow · Hologres 列式分析存储 · 配 covering index 的业务库。","One reconciled, queryable layer feeding downstream BI and analytics; shipped in two weeks while learning the stream stack hands-on.":"一个对过账、可查询的统一层,喂给下游 BI 和分析;一边现学流处理栈,一边在两周内交付。","Every balance change a user sees must be complete, ordered, and fast to query — but the records originate from 10+ heterogeneous systems that disagree on shape, timing, and delivery guarantees. Millions a day arrive through the audited workflow path; the rest stream straight from providers and internal systems, most of which my team didn't own.":"用户看到的每一次余额变动都必须完整、有序、查得快——但记录来自 10+ 个异构系统,它们在形状、时序和投递保证上各说各话。每天数百万笔走带审计的 workflow 路径;其余的直接从 provider 和内部系统流进来,而这些系统大多不归我团队所有。","On top of correctness, there was contention: long-window analytics volume was competing with production reads and writes for the same resources. The platform needed one unified layer where the numbers add up and analytical queries don't slow down production.":"正确性之外还有资源争抢:长窗口的分析量在和生产读写抢同一批资源。平台需要一个统一层,数字加得起来,分析查询也不拖慢生产。","Most sources were owned by other teams, on their own schedules — alignment had to be driven, not assumed.":"大多数来源归其他团队所有,各有各的排期——对齐得靠推动,不能靠假设。","Correctness at the record level: per-user histories had to line up with every source, not just aggregate totals.":"正确性要到单条记录级:每个用户的历史都得和每个来源对得上,不只是总数对得上。","Analytics queries could not contend with production reads and writes for resources.":"分析查询不能和生产读写抢资源。","Two generations of the system were live — every transaction path in both had to be accounted for.":"新旧两代系统同时在线——两边的每一条交易路径都必须盘点在内。","Delivery pressure: the pipeline shipped in two weeks, while learning Hologres and Flink hands-on.":"交付压力:pipeline 两周内上线,还是一边现学 Hologres 和 Flink 一边做的。","I built this pipeline by hand. I scanned every transaction path across two generations of the system, drove the direction for the teams that own each source, composed the stream processor with the durable-workflow engine, and chose the storage split. When historical amounts didn't line up, I reconciled the mismatches record by record. The hard part was cross-team alignment, not code.":"这条 pipeline 是我亲手搭的。我扫遍了新旧两代系统里的每一条交易路径,给各来源的 owner 团队指方向,把流处理器和持久化 workflow 引擎组合起来,并定下存储的拆分。历史金额对不上的时候,我逐条把差异对账补齐。难的是跨团队对齐,不是写代码。","The pipeline composes Flink stream processing with Temporal durable workflows: the audited workflow path delivers millions of records a day, and streaming ingest covers the providers and internal systems beyond it. Source-specific shapes are normalized at the boundary — per-source caching, channel-aware routing — into one canonical row. Storage is split by read pattern: hot recent history stays on the operational store behind covering indexes, while long-window volume flows into a Hologres columnar layer, so analytics never contends with production. Continuous reconciliation sits across both.":"这条 pipeline 把 Flink 流式处理和 Temporal 持久化 workflow 组合起来:带审计的 workflow 路径每天投递数百万条记录,其余的 provider 和内部系统由流式接入覆盖。来源特有的形状在边界处归一化——按来源的缓存、感知渠道的路由——落成一条标准行。存储按读取模式拆分:热的近期历史留在业务库上、配 covering index,长窗口的量流进 Hologres 列式层,分析永远不和生产抢资源。持续对账横跨两边。","source → ingest → normalize → reconcile → query. 10+ sources enter through streaming or the durable workflow path, get normalized at the boundary, are continuously reconciled, and land in a layer that downstream BI and analytics build on.":"来源 → 接入 → 归一化 → 对账 → 查询。10+ 个来源经流式或持久化 workflow 路径进入,在边界处归一化,持续对账,最终落进一个供下游 BI 和分析构建的层。","Walkthrough — a record's journey":"走一遍——一条记录的旅程","a record lands via stream or workflow, in its source's own shape.":"一条记录经流式或 workflow 落地,带着它来源自己的形状。","the boundary adapter maps it to the canonical row — schema differences end here, not downstream.":"边界 adapter 把它映射成标准行——schema 差异到这里为止,不往下游走。","one write to the hot operational store for recent-history reads, one to the columnar layer for analytics.":"一笔写进热的业务库,供近期历史读取;一笔写进列式层,供分析。","daily totals and per-user histories are diffed against the sources; drift is flagged and backfilled, never papered over.":"每日总数和每个用户的历史都和来源做 diff;偏差会被标记并 backfill,绝不糊弄过去。","source → ingest → normalize → reconcile → query":"来源 → 接入 → 归一化 → 对账 → 查询","workflow path":"workflow 路径","at the boundary":"在边界处","hot store":"热存储","recent history":"近期历史","columnar layer":"列式层","analytics · BI":"分析 · BI","reconciliation · daily diff":"对账 · 每日 diff","drift → trace source → fix boundary → backfill":"偏差 → 追溯来源 → 修边界 → backfill","10M+ records/day · climbing":"每天一千万+ 条记录 · 仍在增长","Compose streaming with durable workflows":"把流式和持久化 workflow 组合起来","Force every source through one ingestion mode, or compose two: durable workflows for the audited transaction path, stream processing for everything beyond it.":"把所有来源硬塞进一种接入模式,还是组合两种:带审计的交易路径走持久化 workflow,其余的走流式处理。","Flink and Temporal together — each source enters through the mode that matches its delivery guarantees.":"Flink 和 Temporal 一起用——每个来源走和它投递保证相匹配的那条路。","Sources disagree on shape, timing, and delivery guarantees; one mode would have flattened those differences instead of handling them.":"各来源在形状、时序、投递保证上各说各话;只用一种模式等于把这些差异抹平,而不是处理它们。","Two ingestion paths mean two operational surfaces to run, and reconciliation is what proves they agree.":"两条接入路径意味着要运维两套面;它们是否一致,靠对账来证明。","Split storage by read pattern":"按读取模式拆分存储","Serve everything from the operational store, or split: hot recent history operational, long-window volume in a columnar analytics store.":"全部由业务库来扛,还是拆开:热的近期历史留在业务库,长窗口的量放进列式分析存储。","Hot/cold split — covering indexes for recent-history reads, a Hologres columnar layer fed by the pipeline for analytics.":"冷热拆分——近期历史读取配 covering index,分析走由 pipeline 喂数的 Hologres 列式层。","Long-window analytics volume must not contend with production reads and writes for resources.":"长窗口的分析量不能和生产读写抢资源。","Two stores that must agree — the analytics layer trails the operational store, and reconciliation carries the burden of proving they match.":"两个必须一致的存储——分析层落后于业务库,证明它们相符的担子压在对账上。","Normalize at the boundary, per source":"在边界处按来源归一化","Store raw source shapes and translate at query time, or normalize each source into one canonical row the moment it enters.":"存原始的来源形状、查询时再翻译,还是每个来源一进来就归一化成一条标准行。","Per-source adapters at the boundary — with per-source caching and channel-aware routing — so everything downstream sees one shape.":"边界处按来源做 adapter——配上按来源的缓存和感知渠道的路由——下游看到的永远只有一种形状。","Schema differences handled once at entry cost far less than every consumer re-handling 10+ shapes.":"schema 差异在入口处理一次,远比每个消费方各自处理 10+ 种形状便宜。","Every source quirk becomes boundary code I own; when a source drops, duplicates, or reshapes a record, the fix lands there.":"每个来源的怪癖都变成我要负责的边界代码;来源丢了、重复了或改了记录形状,修复就落在那儿。","The failure mode of an ingestion pipeline is silent: a source drops, duplicates, or reshapes a record and everything keeps running — the numbers are just wrong. Recovery here is built as a permanent process, not an incident response.":"接入 pipeline 的故障模式是无声的:某个来源丢了、重复了或改了一条记录的形状,一切照常运转——只是数字错了。这里的恢复被做成常驻流程,而不是事故响应。","Drift never gets papered over":"偏差绝不糊弄过去","When reconciliation finds a mismatch, the pipeline flags it for backfill rather than adjusting a total to make the books balance. The recovery loop is always the same: trace the drift to the source that caused it, fix the boundary adapter so the class of error can't recur, backfill the affected window, then diff again to confirm. Duplicates and drops are caught the same way — the daily diff is the detection mechanism, and the backfill is the repair.":"对账发现不一致时,pipeline 把它标记待 backfill,而不是调一下总数把账做平。恢复循环永远一样:把偏差追溯到造成它的来源,修好边界 adapter 让这一类错误不再发生,backfill 受影响的窗口,再 diff 一遍确认。重复和丢失也用同一套抓法——每日 diff 是检测机制,backfill 是修复。","Platform practice applies here as everywhere: Jest integration tests run against real databases via Testcontainers rather than mocks, behind an 80% coverage gate, with a weekly full regression across the platform. But the validation that mattered most on this path was the reconciliation itself — one record subtype running as a permanent probe throughout development, daily totals checked against the analytics team's independent numbers, and per-user histories diffed record by record until the sources and the layer agreed.":"平台惯例在这里一样适用:Jest 集成测试通过 Testcontainers 跑真实数据库而不是 mock,卡 80% 覆盖率门槛,每周对全平台跑一次完整回归。但这条路径上最要紧的验证是对账本身——一种记录子类型作为常驻探针贯穿整个开发期,每日总数对上分析团队独立算出的数字,每个用户的历史逐条 diff,直到来源和这个层完全一致。","Freshness vs correctness — a record is queryable as soon as it lands, but proven correct only after reconciliation has diffed it against its source; the daily cross-check is the price of trusting the number.":"新鲜 vs 正确——记录一落地就可查,但要等对账和来源 diff 过才算证明是对的;每日交叉核对是信任这个数字的代价。","Eventual consistency between stores — the columnar layer is fed by the pipeline and trails the operational store; an analytics query can lag the hot path until the sync and the daily diff close the gap.":"存储之间是最终一致——列式层由 pipeline 喂数,落后于业务库;在同步和每日 diff 补上缺口之前,分析查询可能滞后于热路径。","Operational overhead — a stream processor, a workflow engine, and two stores is a lot of surface for one pipeline, and the team adopted the stream stack while shipping on it.":"运维开销——一个流处理器、一个 workflow 引擎、两个存储,对一条 pipeline 来说面不小,而且团队是一边上线一边接手这套流处理栈的。","Source-specific quirks live at the boundary — every adapter encodes one source's behaviour, so each new source, and each source's schema change, is boundary work that someone has to own.":"来源特有的怪癖都住在边界——每个 adapter 编码一个来源的行为,所以每接一个新来源、每次来源改 schema,都是得有人负责的边界活。","Over ten million records a day — and climbing — ingested and queryable through one reconciled layer.":"每天上千万条记录——仍在增长——通过一个对过账的统一层接入并可查询。","Recent-history reads stay fast; long-window analytics stopped competing with production traffic.":"近期历史读取保持快速;长窗口分析不再和生产流量抢资源。","Downstream BI and analytics build on the unified layer instead of chasing 10+ source shapes.":"下游 BI 和分析在统一层上构建,不用再追着 10+ 种来源形状跑。","Historical mismatches reconciled record by record; drift now detected and backfilled as routine.":"历史差异逐条对账补齐;偏差如今作为日常被检测并 backfill。","Shipped in two weeks, learning Hologres and Flink hands-on along the way.":"两周内交付,一路现学 Hologres 和 Flink。","The code is the quick part. On a pipeline like this, the real work is comparing numbers — reconciling record by record against sources other teams own, and driving those teams toward one direction. Correctness isn't a property you declare at launch; it's one you keep re-earning, which is why reconciliation became a permanent part of the system instead of a validation phase. And schema differences are cheapest exactly once, at the boundary — everything downstream should only ever see one shape.":"写代码是快的那部分。这样一条 pipeline 上,真正的活是对数字——和其他团队拥有的来源逐条对账,并推动这些团队走向同一个方向。正确性不是上线时宣布一次的属性,而是要不断重新挣回来的,所以对账成了系统的常驻部分,而不是一个验证阶段。schema 差异恰好在边界处理一次最便宜——下游永远只应该看到一种形状。","Next: Support System →":"下一篇:客服系统 →","case 05 / 08":"案例 05 / 08","Built and ran the platform's reporting for six years, before a dedicated BI team existed — multi-view analytics over million-row datasets, plus regulatory filings delivered on time.":"在专职 BI 团队存在之前,搭建并运营了平台的报表六年——百万行数据集上的多视角分析,外加按时交付的监管报送。","Owner of the reporting function — designed the engine, ran it in production for six years, and delivered every reporting change through it.":"报表职能的 owner——设计了这台引擎,在生产上跑了六年,每一次报表变更都经它交付。","Millions of rows a day; long-window queries over million-row datasets; multi-million-row regulatory filing days.":"每天数百万行;百万行数据集上的长窗口查询;监管报送日达数百万行。","MongoDB aggregation pipelines · precomputed daily summaries · batch settlement workers · streamed FTP delivery.":"MongoDB aggregation pipeline · 预计算的每日汇总 · 批量结算 worker · 流式 FTP 交付。","A working BI function before a BI team existed; 140+ reporting changes over six years; regulatory filings on schedule at million-row scale.":"BI 团队存在之前就有一个能用的 BI 职能;六年 140+ 次报表变更;百万行规模的监管报送按时交付。","Operations, partners, and management all needed data — analytics across multiple views, aggregated over long windows, on the production database — and there was no business-intelligence team to build it. Later, a regulator added a harder requirement: daily filings in exact formats, millions of rows per day, against a hard deadline.":"运营、合作方、管理层都需要数据——多视角的分析、长窗口的聚合,还要跑在生产数据库上——而当时没有 BI 团队来做这件事。后来监管方又加了更硬的要求:按精确格式每日报送,每天数百万行,期限是硬性的。","The two workloads pull in opposite directions. Analytics wants low-latency answers over long windows; regulatory delivery wants complete, correct, multi-million-row files that fit a fixed window. Both had to run against the same primary database without degrading it.":"这两种负载往相反方向拉。分析要的是长窗口上的低延迟答案;监管交付要的是完整、正确、数百万行的文件塞进固定窗口。两者都得跑在同一个主库上,还不能把它拖垮。","Correctness — reporting numbers feed commercial reconciliation, so a fast-but-wrong answer is not an option.":"正确性——报表数字要喂给商务对账,快但错的答案不是选项。","Late corrections — figures can change after the day closes; a frozen snapshot would lock in wrong numbers.":"迟到修正——数字在当日关账后还可能变;冻结的快照会把错的数字锁死。","Hard deadlines — regulatory filings are due daily, in exact formats, regardless of how large the day was.":"硬性期限——监管报送每天都要交,格式精确,不管那天量有多大。","Shared infrastructure — long-window queries run against the primary database and must not starve production traffic.":"共享基础设施——长窗口查询跑在主库上,不能饿死生产流量。","No dedicated team — one engineering function had to cover operational, analytical, and compliance reporting.":"没有专职团队——一个工程职能要覆盖运营、分析、合规三种报表。","I built and ran the platform's reporting for six years, before a dedicated BI team existed. That meant owning the whole surface: multi-view analytics for operations, partners, and management; operational reporting; and the regulatory filing pipeline with its daily deadline. Every one of the 140+ reporting changes over that period shipped through this engine. When a formal BI team was eventually stood up, it built on these foundations.":"平台的报表是我搭的、也是我跑了六年的——那时还没有专职 BI 团队。这意味着整个面都归我:给运营、合作方、管理层的多视角分析;运营报表;还有带每日死线的监管报送 pipeline。那段时间的 140+ 次报表变更,每一次都经这台引擎交付。后来正式的 BI 团队组建起来,就是在这套地基上继续建的。","A precompute + recompute dual track. An independent settlement process streams per-user transaction flows to workers in batches and lands precomputed daily summaries — the materialized layer reads are served from. A recompute window stays open behind the current day, so late corrections still land instead of freezing a wrong number. Ad-hoc queries run tuned aggregation pipelines; the scheduler was rewritten to make the 2-day recompute window reliable. Regulatory delivery is a separate pipeline off the settled data: million-row-per-file slicing with append-based FTP upload, streamed so multi-million-row days fit the filing window.":"预计算 + 重算的双轨。一个独立的结算进程把每个用户的交易流按 batch 推给 worker,落成预计算的每日汇总——读取就是从这个物化层出的。当日之后留一个重算窗口,迟到修正照样能落进去,而不是把错的数字冻住。临时查询走调优过的 aggregation pipeline;调度器被重写,让 2 天重算窗口跑得可靠。监管交付是从结算数据分出来的另一条 pipeline:按每文件一百万行切片、FTP append 上传,全程流式,几百万行的日子也能塞进报送窗口。","Query flow":"查询流程","A report request splits at the recompute cutoff: settled days are read straight from precomputed summaries; the recent window is aggregated live; the two tracks merge into one answer. Fast where the data is stable, correct where it is still moving.":"一次报表请求在重算分界点分开:已结算的日子直接读预计算汇总;最近的窗口实时聚合;两条轨合并成一个答案。数据稳定的地方快,数据还在动的地方对。","Aggregation strategy":"聚合策略","Precompute what repeats — daily summaries per view, landed by batch settlement workers off per-user transaction streams. Only ad-hoc shapes hit the primary database live, through tuned aggregation pipelines rather than raw long-window scans.":"重复的就预计算——每个视角的每日汇总,由批量结算 worker 从每用户交易流落成。只有临时的查询形状实时打到主库,而且走调优过的 aggregation pipeline,不做裸的长窗口扫描。","Regulatory delivery":"监管交付","Filing days stream in batches from the settled data, roll to a new file at a million rows, and upload by FTP append — constant memory, tuned until multi-million-row days fit the delivery window.":"报送日从结算数据按 batch 流出,满一百万行滚到新文件,FTP append 上传——内存恒定,一路调到几百万行的日子也能塞进交付窗口。","Precompute + recompute, not one or the other":"预计算 + 重算,不二选一","Query everything live on the primary database, freeze daily snapshots and never revisit them, or run both tracks — precomputed summaries plus a live recompute window.":"全部实时查主库、冻结每日快照从不回头,还是两条轨一起跑——预计算汇总加一个活的重算窗口。","The dual track: read precomputed daily summaries for latency, keep a recompute window open so late corrections still land.":"双轨:读预计算的每日汇总保延迟,留一个重算窗口让迟到修正照样落地。","Reporting numbers feed commercial reconciliation. Pure live queries can't hold latency over long windows at million-row scale; frozen snapshots lock in wrong numbers when figures move after the day closes.":"报表数字要喂给商务对账。百万行规模下,纯实时查询在长窗口上撑不住延迟;而数字在关账后还会动,冻结快照会把错的数字锁死。","Two read paths and a merge at the cutoff — more moving parts than either extreme, and a recompute schedule that has to run reliably.":"两条读路径加分界点上的合并——比任何一个极端都多的活动部件,还有一个必须可靠运转的重算排程。","An independent settlement process, not read-time computation":"独立的结算进程,而不是读时计算","Compute summaries on the read path when a report is requested, or run a separate settlement process that streams per-user transaction flows to workers in batches and lands the summaries ahead of time.":"在报表被请求时在读路径上算汇总,还是跑一个独立的结算进程,把每用户交易流按 batch 推给 worker,提前把汇总落好。","The independent settlement process. Reads serve materialized summaries; the heavy aggregation happens once, off the request path.":"独立的结算进程。读取直接出物化汇总;重的聚合只发生一次,而且不在请求路径上。","Long-window aggregation at read time would put the full cost on every request and on the primary database at the worst moment — when someone is waiting.":"读时做长窗口聚合,等于把全部成本压到每一次请求上、压到主库上,而且是在最糟的时刻——有人正在等。","Freshness depends on the scheduler, which became load-bearing — it had to be rewritten to make the 2-day recompute window reliable.":"新鲜度取决于调度器,它因此成了承重件——不得不重写,才让 2 天重算窗口跑得可靠。","Stream and slice filings, never buffer a day":"报送流式切片,绝不整天缓存","Build each filing day as one file in memory and upload it whole, or stream settled rows in batches, slice at a million rows per file, and upload by FTP append.":"把一个报送日整份文件在内存里拼好再整体上传,还是把结算行按 batch 流出,每文件一百万行切片,FTP append 上传。","Stream, slice at one million rows per file, append-upload.":"流式,每文件一百万行切片,append 上传。","A multi-million-row day has to fit a fixed filing window under constant memory; buffering the whole day doesn't scale with the data and gives no room to tune.":"几百万行的一天必须在恒定内存下塞进固定的报送窗口;整天缓存跟不上数据增长,也没有调优的余地。","Batch sizes became a tuning surface — throughput had to be adjusted until the largest days fit the window — and append-based upload needs care around partial writes.":"batch 大小成了调优面——吞吐得一路调到最大的日子也能塞进窗口——而 append 式上传要小心部分写入的问题。","The design exists to absorb three specific failure modes.":"这套设计就是为了吸收三种具体的故障模式。","Late corrections:":"迟到修正:","figures that change after a day closes land through the open recompute window instead of silently diverging from a frozen summary.":"关账后还在变的数字,经开着的重算窗口落地,而不是和冻结的汇总悄悄分叉。","Unreliable recompute runs:":"重算跑得不可靠:","the original scheduler couldn't be trusted with a window that reconciliation depends on, so it was rewritten until the 2-day recompute cycle ran reliably.":"原来的调度器托不起一个对账要依赖的窗口,于是被重写,直到 2 天重算周期跑得可靠。","Oversized filing days:":"报送日超量:","when a day's volume grows past what a single pass can handle, the answer is in the pipeline's shape — streamed batches, per-file slicing, and append upload were tuned until multi-million-row days still fit the delivery window.":"当一天的量涨过单趟能扛的上限,答案在 pipeline 的形状里——流式 batch、按文件切片、append 上传,一路调到几百万行的日子仍然塞得进交付窗口。","Reporting follows the platform's testing practice: Jest with integration tests against real dependencies via Testcontainers, plus a weekly regression pass. The properties that matter here are the seams — that the merge at the recompute cutoff neither drops nor double-counts a day, and that the filing slicer rolls files at exactly the row limit.":"报表遵循平台的测试惯例:Jest 配 Testcontainers 跑真实依赖的集成测试,外加每周一轮回归。这里真正要紧的性质在接缝上——重算分界点的合并既不丢一天也不重复算一天,报送切片器精确在行数上限处滚文件。","The dual track buys speed and correctness at the cost of two read paths — settled summaries and live aggregation — that have to agree at the cutoff, forever.":"双轨用两条读路径的代价换来又快又对——结算汇总和实时聚合,得在分界点上永远保持一致。","Precomputation ties report freshness to the settlement schedule; the scheduler became critical infrastructure and had to be rewritten to earn that role.":"预计算把报表的新鲜度绑在结算排程上;调度器成了关键基础设施,也是靠重写才配得上这个角色。","Streaming with append-based upload keeps memory constant but makes delivery a tuning exercise: batch sizes were adjusted until the largest days fit the filing window, and would need retuning if volume kept growing.":"流式加 append 上传让内存保持恒定,但把交付变成了调优活:batch 大小一路调到最大的日子能塞进报送窗口,量再涨还得重调。","Everything runs against the primary database rather than a dedicated analytics store — workable at this scale with tuned pipelines and precompute, but it is a ceiling, not a permanent answer.":"一切都跑在主库上而不是专门的分析存储——在这个规模下,靠调优过的 pipeline 和预计算还行得通,但这是一块天花板,不是永久答案。","The platform had a working BI function before it had a BI team; the formal team later built on these foundations.":"平台在拥有 BI 团队之前,就先有了一个能用的 BI 职能;后来正式的团队在这套地基上继续建。","Regulatory filings shipped on schedule at million-row scale — millions of rows a day, hard deadlines met.":"监管报送在百万行规模上按时交付——每天数百万行,硬性期限全部达成。","140+ reporting changes delivered over six years across operational, analytical, and compliance reporting.":"六年里交付 140+ 次报表变更,覆盖运营、分析、合规三类报表。","Reads served from precomputed summaries instead of long-window scans, with late corrections still landing through the recompute window.":"读取由预计算汇总出,而不是长窗口扫描;迟到修正照样经重算窗口落地。","When numbers feed reconciliation, speed and correctness aren't a trade to make — the architecture has to buy both, and the dual track is what that costs: precompute for latency, a recompute window for truth. The unglamorous parts carry the system — the scheduler and the batch tuning got no design credit, but the deadlines were met or missed there. And reporting built under constraint doesn't have to be throwaway: done with clear seams, it becomes the foundation the dedicated team inherits rather than the mess they replace.":"当数字要喂给对账,快和对就不是一道选择题——架构必须两个都买下,双轨就是那个价钱:预计算换延迟,重算窗口换真相。撑起系统的是不起眼的部分——调度器和 batch 调优拿不到设计上的荣誉,但期限是在那里达成或错过的。受限条件下做出来的报表也不必是用完即弃的:接缝做干净,它就成了专职团队接手的地基,而不是他们要替换的烂摊子。","Next: AI Delivery Pipeline →":"下一篇:AI 交付 pipeline →","case 04 / 08":"案例 04 / 08","Built from zero on a stack new to the company — AI-assisted handling with human takeover — grown to a team and handed off clean.":"在公司全新的技术栈上从零做起——AI 辅助处理、人工接管——养成一个团队后干净交接。","Built it solo from zero, grew the team to two, then handed the service off — first to a maintenance team, later to the AI team.":"一个人从零做起,团队扩到两人,然后把服务交接出去——先给维护团队,后来给 AI 团队。","Real-time customer conversations for the platform; AI designed to absorb roughly 70% of repetitive inquiries, humans take the rest.":"平台的实时客户会话;AI 设计目标是消化大约七成的重复性咨询,剩下的归人。","NestJS · gRPC · Temporal · Pulsar · Redis · a self-hosted off-the-shelf messaging backbone as transport.":"NestJS · gRPC · Temporal · Pulsar · Redis · self-hosted 的现成 messaging backbone 做传输层。","First production service on the new stack; its patterns became the template later services copied. Runs today as standalone multi-channel middleware.":"新栈上的第一个生产服务;它立下的模式成了后续服务照抄的模板。如今作为独立的多渠道中间件在跑。","The platform needed a real-time support channel and had none. At the same time, the company had just decided on a new microservices stack — NestJS, gRPC, Temporal, Pulsar — that no one had shipped to production yet. I was handed both problems at once: build the support system, and prove the stack on the way.":"平台需要一个实时客服渠道,当时一个都没有。与此同时,公司刚定下新的微服务栈——NestJS、gRPC、Temporal、Pulsar——还没人把它上过生产。两个问题一起塞给了我:把客服系统做出来,顺路证明这套栈可行。","This was the pilot the whole stack migration was judged on. Whatever patterns it set — good or bad — later services would inherit.":"整个栈迁移的成败就看这个 pilot。它立下的模式——不管好坏——后续服务都会继承。","Solo start — one engineer, no existing service on the stack to copy from.":"单人起步——一个工程师,栈上没有任何现成服务可抄。","Every piece of the stack was new to me at once: NestJS, gRPC, Temporal, Pulsar, and the messaging backbone.":"栈里每一块对我都是同时上手的新东西:NestJS、gRPC、Temporal、Pulsar,还有 messaging backbone。","The outcome would decide whether the company's migration to the new stack was viable.":"做出来的结果,直接决定公司向新栈迁移是否可行。","The message transport was fixed — the framework choice was the CTO's call; the data model and flows were mine to design.":"消息传输层是定死的——选框架是 CTO 的决定;数据模型和流程由我来设计。","The AI could not be trusted in the critical path without an exit: a stalled model must never leave a customer waiting.":"AI 不能没有退路地待在关键路径上:模型卡住了,绝不能让客户干等。","I built the initial production version alone: the data model, the conversation flows, the agent-routing queue, the AI handoff path, and the operational patterns around them. As the system grew I brought in a second engineer, then handed the service off — first to a maintenance team, later to the AI team — and they run it independently today. The handoff was part of the job, not an afterthought: the service had to be operable by people who didn't build it.":"最初的生产版本是我一个人做的:数据模型、会话流程、客服路由队列、AI handoff 路径,以及围绕它们的运维模式。系统长大后我招进第二个工程师,然后把服务交接出去——先给维护团队,后来给 AI 团队——如今他们独立运营。交接是工作本身的一部分,不是事后补的:这个服务必须能由没参与搭建的人来运维。","Buy the base, build the differentiators. I self-hosted an off-the-shelf messaging backbone as the message transport and built only what it doesn't have: an agent-routing queue that encodes the whole assignment policy — status first, load second, longest-wait tie-break — into a single Redis sorted-set score; a mini back-office view so agents see a member's account records, top-up / withdrawal history and permissions in one screen instead of switching systems; and an AI-first answer path with a 10-second race guard that hands the chat to a human whenever the model stalls or errors.":"买底座,自建差异化层。我 self-hosted 一套现成的 messaging backbone 做消息传输,只自建它没有的东西:一个客服路由队列,把整套派单策略——先看状态、再看负载、等最久者决胜——编码进一个 Redis sorted-set 分数;一个迷你后台视图,让客服在一个屏幕里看到用户的账户记录、充值/提现历史和权限,不用来回切系统;还有一条 AI 先答的路径,配 10 秒竞速保护,模型一卡壳或报错就把会话交给人。","Routing queue":"路由队列","The score is banded so status always outranks load, and load outranks waiting time. Every agent state change is one atomic increment; assignment just reads the head of the queue — O(1), no scan, no race.":"分数分段,状态永远压过负载,负载永远压过等待时长。客服每次状态变化都是一次原子自增;派单只需要读队头——O(1),不扫描,没竞态。","AI first, human takeover":"AI 先答,人工接管","AI answers first — designed to absorb the repetitive share of inquiries, roughly 70%. Every model call races a ten-second timer; on stall, error or timeout the conversation goes straight to a human via the routing queue. A per-room lock gives each conversation exactly one owner: the first invite wins, duplicates walk away.":"AI 先答——设计目标是消化重复性的那部分咨询,大约七成。每次模型调用都和一个十秒计时器竞速;一卡壳、报错或超时,会话就经路由队列直接交给人。per-room 锁保证每个会话恰好一个 owner:先到的邀请赢,重复的走开。","Buy the base, build the differentiators":"买底座,自建差异化层","Build the message transport from scratch, or self-host an off-the-shelf messaging backbone and build only what it doesn't have.":"从零自研消息传输层,还是 self-host 一套现成的 messaging backbone,只补它没有的东西。","Self-host the backbone as transport (the framework was the CTO's call; the data model and flows were mine). Build the routing queue, the agent back-office view, and the AI handoff in-house.":"Self-host 这套 backbone 做传输层(选框架是 CTO 的决定;数据模型和流程是我的)。路由队列、客服后台视图、AI handoff 全部自建。","Message delivery is a solved problem; agent routing, one-screen member context, and AI-with-takeover are where the product actually differs.":"消息投递是个已解决的问题;客服路由、一屏看全的用户上下文、带接管的 AI,才是产品真正不同的地方。","Operating third-party infrastructure we didn't write — its room and event model shaped how our flows had to be expressed, and its production behaviour was ours to learn.":"运维不是我们写的第三方基础设施——它的房间和事件模型决定了我们的流程只能怎么表达,它在生产上的脾气也得我们自己摸。","Routing policy as one banded score":"路由策略压成一个分段分数","Scan and rank agents on every assignment, or encode the whole policy into a single sortable number.":"每次派单都扫描并排序所有客服,还是把整套策略编码进一个可排序的数字。","One Redis sorted-set score, banded so each term owns an order of magnitude: status first, load second, longest-wait tie-break. Assignment reads the head of the set.":"一个 Redis sorted-set 分数,分段让每一项各占一个数量级:先看状态、再看负载、等最久者决胜。派单读集合的头。","Every agent state change becomes one atomic increment — no read-modify-write race — and picking the next agent is O(1).":"客服每次状态变化都变成一次原子自增——没有 read-modify-write 竞态——挑下一位客服是 O(1)。","The policy is compressed into an encoding: bands must never overflow into each other, and reading the queue means knowing the scheme. The banding later paid for itself when the Redis cluster rejected transactions — pure atomic increments were already enough.":"策略被压缩成一套编码:分段之间绝不能互相溢出,读这个队列就得懂这套方案。这个分段设计后来在 Redis cluster 拒绝事务的那天回了本——纯原子自增已经够用了。","AI answers first — behind a hard exit":"AI 先答——但备着一条硬退路","Use the model as a suggestion tool for agents, or let it answer customers directly with humans as the escalation path.":"把模型当客服的建议工具,还是让它直接回答客户、人作为升级路径。","AI first, designed to absorb the repetitive share of inquiries — roughly 70% — with every model call raced against a ten-second timer and any stall, error or timeout handed straight to a human.":"AI 先答,设计目标是消化重复性的那部分咨询——大约七成——每次模型调用都和十秒计时器竞速,一卡壳、报错或超时就直接交给人。","Most inquiries are repetitive; the ones that aren't need a person anyway. Treating the model as a flaky third-party dependency — timeout, fallback, never in the critical path without an exit — makes the design safe either way.":"大多数咨询是重复性的;不重复的那些反正也需要人。把模型当成一个不可靠的第三方依赖——超时、降级、绝不无退路地放进关键路径——不管哪种情况设计都是安全的。","AI answering first means AI failing first: the escalation path has to be bulletproof, and the concurrency in that path — duplicate invites, racing score updates — turned out to be the hardest engineering on the project.":"AI 先答就意味着 AI 先挂:升级路径必须无懈可击,而这条路径上的并发——重复邀请、竞速的分数更新——成了整个项目最难的工程。","AI answering first means AI failing first. Every model call races a ten-second timer, and on stall, error or timeout the conversation is handed straight to a human — the user always ends up with a person, never with a spinner. The model gets treated like any flaky third-party dependency: timeout, fallback, and never in the critical path without an exit. That guard fired in production more than once, and nobody noticed — which was the point. The service's structured logging is what made that verifiable after the fact: the fallbacks are in the logs, not in the complaints.":"AI 先答就意味着 AI 先挂。每次模型调用都和十秒计时器竞速,一卡壳、报错或超时,会话就直接交给人——用户最终面对的永远是一个人,而不是一个转圈的加载图标。模型享受的是不可靠第三方依赖的待遇:超时、降级、绝不无退路地放进关键路径。这道保护在生产上触发过不止一次,而没人察觉——这正是重点。事后能验证这一点,靠的是服务的结构化日志:降级记录在日志里,而不是在投诉里。","The service follows the platform's test discipline: Jest with integration tests running against real dependencies via Testcontainers — the lock and score behaviour is concurrency-dependent, so it's exercised against a real Redis, not a mock — behind an 80% coverage gate and a weekly regression run. The tests that matter most here fire the same trigger twice: two simultaneous invites into one room must produce exactly one assigned agent, and a model call that never returns must land the conversation on a human within the guard window.":"服务遵循平台的测试纪律:Jest 配 Testcontainers 对真实依赖跑集成测试——锁和分数的行为依赖并发,所以是对真实的 Redis 练的,不是 mock——卡 80% 覆盖率门槛,每周跑一轮回归。这里最要紧的测试是把同一个触发器打两次:同一房间同时进来两个邀请,必须恰好产生一位被派单的客服;一次永不返回的模型调用,必须在保护窗口内把会话落到人身上。","Self-hosting an off-the-shelf backbone meant operating infrastructure we didn't write — its room and event model constrained how our flows were expressed, in exchange for not rebuilding message delivery.":"Self-host 一套现成的 backbone,意味着运维不是我们写的基础设施——它的房间和事件模型限制了我们流程的表达方式,换来的是不用重造消息投递。","Compressing the routing policy into one banded score makes assignment O(1) and race-free, but couples the policy to an encoding: the bands are a contract, and changing the policy means changing the scheme.":"把路由策略压进一个分段分数,让派单 O(1) 且无竞态,但也把策略和编码耦合在一起:分段是一份契约,改策略就得改方案。","AI answering first pushed real engineering cost into the escalation path — the race guard, the per-room lock, the atomic queue updates all exist because the fallback has to be more reliable than the model it backs.":"AI 先答把真正的工程成本推进了升级路径——竞速保护、per-room 锁、原子的队列更新之所以存在,都是因为降级路径必须比它兜底的模型更可靠。","Being the first service on the stack meant setting patterns while still learning it; some of that learning happened in production, which is where the war stories above come from.":"作为栈上的第一个服务,意味着一边学一边立模式;有些学费是在生产上交的,上面那些战争故事就是这么来的。","First production service on the company's new stack — the migration's viability was proven on it.":"公司新栈上的第一个生产服务——迁移的可行性就是在它身上证明的。","Its patterns — config via Vault, contract-first gRPC, structured logging, graceful shutdown — became the pattern reference later services copied.":"它立下的模式——配置走 Vault、契约先行的 gRPC、结构化日志、graceful shutdown——成了后续服务照抄的模式参考。","AI-assisted handling designed to absorb roughly 70% of repetitive inquiries, with silent human takeover when the model stalls or errors.":"AI 辅助处理,设计目标是消化约 70% 的重复性咨询;模型卡壳或报错时,人无声接管。","Grew from a solo build to a two-person team, then a clean handoff — first to a maintenance team, later to the AI team, who run it independently.":"从单人搭建长成两人团队,然后干净交接——先给维护团队,后来给 AI 团队,如今由他们独立运营。","Runs today as a standalone multi-channel middleware.":"如今作为独立的多渠道中间件在跑。","Buy the commodity and build the differentiator — the transport was never where this project's value was. Anything triggered by \"a message arrived\" will eventually fire twice in the same millisecond, so conversation ownership has to be a fence, not a convention. A model in the critical path is a flaky dependency and gets a flaky dependency's treatment: timeout, fallback, exit. And a fix isn't done until it survives the real production topology — the banded score design was worth more on the day the cluster rejected transactions than on the day it was drawn. Finally, patterns set by a first service outlive the service: the most durable output here wasn't the support system, it was the template everything after it copied.":"买下商品化的部分,自建差异化的部分——传输层从来不是这个项目的价值所在。任何由「来了一条消息」触发的东西,终有一天会在同一毫秒触发两次,所以会话的所有权必须是一道栅栏,而不是一条约定。关键路径上的模型就是一个不可靠依赖,就按不可靠依赖来伺候:超时、降级、退路。一个修复没在真实的生产拓扑里活下来就不算完——分段分数的设计,在 cluster 拒绝事务的那天,比画出来的那天更值钱。最后,第一个服务立下的模式比服务本身活得久:这里最耐久的产出不是客服系统,而是后来一切照抄的那个模板。","Next: Reporting Engine →":"下一篇:报表引擎 →","case 06 / 08":"案例 06 / 08","AI Delivery":"AI 交付","A staged delivery pipeline where AI drafts and humans gate every merge — built for a small team with a growing backlog.":"一条分阶段的交付 pipeline:AI 起草,每一次 merge 都由人把关——为一个 backlog 不断增长的小团队而建。","Designed and built the pipeline, its skills and its review agents; my team ships through it.":"设计并搭建了这条 pipeline、它的 skills 和 review agents;我的团队通过它交付。","10 pipeline stages · 23 skills · 12 role agents · a routing manifest across 17 repositories.":"10 个 pipeline 阶段 · 23 个 skills · 12 个角色 agents · 一份横跨 17 个仓库的路由清单。","Agent skills (Markdown policies) · MCP · proto-first contracts · content-hash artifact state.":"Agent skills(Markdown 策略)· MCP · proto 先行的契约 · 基于内容哈希的产物状态。","16 features shipped through it; feature first drafts went from days to hours. Nothing merges without human sign-off.":"16 个功能经它上线;功能初稿从几天压到几小时。没有人签核,任何东西都不能 merge。","A small backend team, a backlog that grows faster than headcount, and AI tools that produce plausible-but-wrong output when used casually. Unmanaged agent use had real costs: an agent \"fixed\" a harmless legacy bug that other code depended on and broke production behaviour; another answered a one-condition change with hundreds of new lines; another updated a database row by row — correct, and an IO storm at our volume.":"一个小后端团队,backlog 涨得比人手快,而 AI 工具随手一用就会产出「像样但错误」的结果。不加管理的 agent 使用有过真实代价:一个 agent「修好」了一个无害的 legacy bug,而其他代码悄悄依赖着它,生产行为直接被打破;另一个 agent 面对一处只加一个条件的改动,回了几百行新代码;还有一个逐行更新数据库——正确,但在我们的量级上就是一场 IO 风暴。","The pattern behind all of these: damage happens when someone can't yet tell a good answer from a plausible one. The problem to solve was not \"use AI more\" — it was making AI output safe to ship.":"这些事故背后是同一个模式:当一个人还分不清「好答案」和「像样的答案」时,损害就会发生。要解决的问题不是「多用 AI」,而是让 AI 的产出可以安全上线。","Nothing irreversible without a human: commit, publish, deploy, migration all require explicit confirmation.":"没有人参与,任何不可逆的事都不会发生:commit、publish、deploy、migration 都需要明确确认。","Contract discipline — producers and consumers must not drift, so contracts are generated and shared before code is written.":"契约纪律——生产者和消费者不能漂移,所以契约在写代码之前就生成并共享。","Finite context — a model can't hold 17 repositories; relevance had to be engineered, not hoped for.":"有限的 context——模型装不下 17 个仓库;「相关」必须靠工程做出来,不能靠指望。","Auditability — every stage's output is a reviewable artifact with an approval signature.":"可审计——每个阶段的产出都是一份带批准签名、可 review 的产物。","Junior safety — the pipeline had to protect people still building the discernment to judge AI output.":"junior 的安全——pipeline 必须保护那些判断力还在成长、尚不足以评判 AI 产出的人。","Role and responsibility":"角色与职责","I designed the pipeline, wrote the stage skills and agent remits, and set the governance rules the team runs under. Some building blocks were adopted from the community and adapted — credited, not claimed. The delivery pipeline, the review roles and the repo router were built from scratch. The team uses it daily; I maintain it.":"pipeline 是我设计的,各阶段的 skills 和 agent 职责是我写的,团队运行所遵循的治理规则也是我定的。有些构件是从社区拿来再改造的——署名,不冒领。交付 pipeline、review 角色和 repo 路由是从零自建的。团队每天在用,我在维护。","A one-line feature request walks through ten artifact-gated stages: requirements draft → design proposal → human design approval → contract generation → SDK update → task breakdown → parallel implementation by subagents → machine-judged verification against the contracts. There is no state database — every stage derives its state from the presence and content hash of the artifact the previous stage wrote, and refuses to run until that artifact exists and is approved.":"一句话的功能请求,要走完十个以产物为门禁的阶段:需求草稿 → 设计提案 → 人工设计批准 → 契约生成 → SDK 更新 → 任务拆解 → subagent 并行实现 → 按契约做机器判定的验证。没有状态数据库——每个阶段的状态,都由上一阶段写下的那份产物的存在与内容哈希推导出来;那份产物不存在、没批准,这个阶段就拒绝运行。","What AI drafts:":"AI 起草什么:","requirements documents (unknowns marked \"to confirm\" instead of guessed), design proposals, contracts, task breakdowns, implementation, review feedback.":"需求文档(不确定的地方标「待确认」而不是靠猜)、设计提案、契约、任务拆解、实现、review 意见。","What humans own:":"人握着什么:","the design approval gate, every merge, and every irreversible action.":"设计批准这道门、每一次 merge,以及每一个不可逆的动作。","What can never happen automatically:":"什么永远不会自动发生:","commit, publish, deploy, migration.":"commit、publish、deploy、migration。","Key decisions":"关键决策","Artifact-gated state, no state database":"以产物为门禁的状态,不设状态数据库","Track pipeline progress in a state store, or derive state from the artifacts themselves.":"把 pipeline 进度记在一个状态存储里,还是直接从产物本身推导状态。","Content-hash state: each stage hashes the upstream artifact and detects changes.":"内容哈希状态:每个阶段对上游产物做哈希、检出改动。","Edits ripple forward deterministically; re-running a stage is always safe, and the artifact trail doubles as the audit trail.":"修改会确定性地向前传导;重跑任何阶段都是安全的,产物链同时兼任审计链。","Ceremony — even a small change walks the stages, which can feel heavy for one-line fixes.":"仪式感——再小的改动也要走完这些阶段,对一行的修复来说会显得重。","Specialist reviewers, not one generalist agent":"专职 reviewer,而不是一个全能 agent","One agent that does everything, or twelve role agents with tight remits and separate tool budgets.":"一个什么都干的 agent,还是十二个职责收紧、工具预算各自独立的角色 agents。","Role specialists — planner, architect, developers, reviewers, QA, security auditor and more. None can approve its own work.":"角色专精——planner、架构师、开发、reviewer、QA、安全审计等等。谁都不能批准自己的工作。","Each role draws a boundary; review quality comes from the separation, the same way it does in a human team.":"每个角色都画出一条边界;review 质量来自这种分离,和人类团队是同一个道理。","More invocations and more harness maintenance than a single-agent setup.":"比单 agent 方案多出更多次调用、更多 harness 维护。","Contracts before code":"契约先于代码","Let implementation drive the interfaces, or generate and publish contracts before a line of code is written.":"让实现来驱动接口,还是在写下第一行代码之前就生成并发布契约。","Contract-first: the design stage produces the API and data contracts; the SDK consumes them before development starts.":"契约先行:设计阶段产出 API 和数据契约;开发开始之前,SDK 就先消费它们。","Producers and consumers can't drift, and machine-judged acceptance has something objective to judge against.":"生产者和消费者不可能漂移,机器判定的验收也有了客观的判定依据。","Upfront design cost on features where the contract is trivial.":"在契约本来就很简单的功能上,要提前付一笔设计成本。","Failure modes and recovery":"故障模式与恢复","The discipline came from the failures — these are the ones that shaped the rules.":"纪律是从失败里来的——下面这些,就是塑造了规则的那几次。","The agent found a real bug — one that had sat harmless in production for years — and repaired it. The repair changed behaviour other code had quietly grown to depend on, and things blew up. An agent evaluates code; it doesn't know your system's history. A harmless bug is load-bearing until proven otherwise.":"agent 找到了一个真实的 bug——在生产里无害地躺了好几年的那种——并把它修了。这一修改变了其他代码早已悄悄依赖的行为,东西就炸了。agent 评估的是代码;它不了解你系统的历史。一个无害的 bug,在证明并非如此之前,都要当它是承重的。","The requirement was genuinely small — an existing rule needed one more condition, a change the codebase was already shaped for. The agent, not grasping that intent, rebuilt the surrounding flow instead: hundreds of new lines that technically worked and doubled the review burden. The smallest correct change comes from knowing what the codebase already wants to do — that judgment is still ours.":"需求确实很小——一条现有规则要多加一个条件,代码库本来就为这种改动留好了形状。agent 没有领会这个意图,反而把周边流程重建了一遍:几百行技术上能跑的新代码,review 负担直接翻倍。最小的正确改动,来自知道代码库本来想怎么做——这个判断,仍然归我们。","Asked for accuracy, the agent updated the database row by row — correct, and an IO storm at our volume. Batching was the obvious answer, but only obvious to someone who has paid for IO before. Performance instincts don't ship with the model; they come from the scars.":"为了准确,agent 逐行更新数据库——正确,但在我们的量级上就是一场 IO 风暴。批量处理是显然的答案,但只对为 IO 付过代价的人显然。性能直觉不随模型出厂;它来自伤疤。","How failures become policy":"失败如何变成规则","Each of these compiled into the pipeline: a production lesson becomes a rule wired into the agent harness — a readiness gate the agent can't skip — so the same mistake can't ship twice. The rule is not \"use AI less.\" It is: discernment first, delegation second.":"这几次都被编译进了 pipeline:一条生产教训变成一条接进 agent harness 的规则——一道 agent 跳不过去的就绪门禁——同一个错误就不可能上线第二次。规则不是「少用 AI」,而是:判断力在先,委派在后。","Representative artifact":"代表性产物","Real excerpt from the pipeline repo — desensitized (neutral service names, no company internals). Each stage and building block is a skill: a Markdown policy the agent reads before it acts. This one came out of a real incident.":"来自 pipeline 仓库的真实节选——已脱敏(服务名做了中性化,没有公司内部信息)。每个阶段和构件都是一个 skill:一份 agent 动手之前先读的 Markdown 策略。这一份,就出自一次真实事故。","Testing and validation":"测试与验证","The final stage is machine-judged acceptance against the contracts generated at design time — objective criteria, not vibes. Code produced through the pipeline still passes the same bar as any other code on the platform: review by the role agents and by humans, the coverage gate, and the weekly full regression before release. Every artifact carries a human approval signature before the next stage will run.":"最后一个阶段是按设计时生成的契约做机器判定的验收——客观标准,不是感觉。经 pipeline 产出的代码,仍然要过和平台上其他代码同一条线:角色 agents 加人工的 review、覆盖率门禁、发版前的每周全量回归。每份产物都要带上人工批准签名,下一阶段才会运行。","Review burden is real: AI multiplies draft volume, and every line still needs a human who can judge it.":"review 负担是真实的:AI 把草稿量成倍放大,而每一行仍然需要一个能评判它的人。","Hallucination risk never reaches zero — the gates reduce blast radius; they don't remove the need for discernment.":"幻觉风险永远到不了零——门禁缩小的是爆炸半径,替代不了判断力。","Context quality is a standing maintenance cost: the routing manifest and 30+ per-service context files have to stay current or the agent starts every task wrong.":"context 质量是一笔长期维护成本:路由清单和 30+ 份 per-service context 文件必须保持最新,否则 agent 每个任务一开工就是错的。","Skills and agent remits are code too — 23 skills need versioning, review and upkeep.":"skills 和 agent 职责也是代码——23 个 skills 需要版本管理、review 和日常维护。","False confidence is the quiet failure mode: output that looks right invites rubber-stamping, which is why no agent can approve its own work.":"虚假的信心是最安静的失败模式:看起来对的产出会引人盖橡皮章,所以没有任何 agent 能批准自己的工作。","16 features shipped through the pipeline.":"16 个功能经这条 pipeline 上线。","Feature first drafts compressed from days to hours — a two-day build becomes a two-hour first draft; the last twenty percent is still ours.":"功能初稿从几天压到几小时——两天的活变成两小时的初稿;最后那百分之二十仍然归我们。","No unreviewed merge: every stage produces a signed-off artifact before the next runs.":"没有未经 review 的 merge:每个阶段都先产出一份签核过的产物,下一阶段才会跑。","Production lessons compile into pipeline policy, so the same mistake can't ship twice.":"生产教训被编译进 pipeline 规则,同一个错误不可能上线第二次。","What I learned":"我学到什么","AI amplifies your code culture — an agent raised on a disciplined codebase ships discipline; raised on mess, it ships mess faster. Context beats prompts: the agent should start every task already knowing the codebase, not be talked into it per request. And the human skill that matters most is discernment — you must be able to judge the problem and the logic before you outsource the typing.":"AI 放大的是你的代码文化——在有纪律的代码库里长大的 agent,交付的就是纪律;在烂摊子里长大,它只会更快地交付烂摊子。context 胜过 prompt:agent 接到任何任务时就该已经认识代码库,而不是每次请求都靠说服。而人最要紧的本事是判断力——在把打字外包出去之前,你必须先能评判问题和逻辑本身。","Next: Multi-Currency & Crypto Integration →":"下一篇:多币种与加密货币集成 →","case 07 / 08":"案例 07 / 08","Multi-Currency &":"多币种与","Payment integration where a precision slip is a real loss — deposits, withdrawals and transfers threaded through every transaction boundary.":"一次精度失误就是真实损失的支付集成——充值、提现、转账,织进每一个交易边界。","Drove the payments side for two years as half of a two-engineer pair, alongside the team's assistant lead.":"支付这条线我推了两年,和团队的副手搭档,两个工程师负责。","Every payment flow on the platform — deposits, withdrawals, transfers — with fiat↔USDT conversion at every transaction boundary.":"平台上的每一条支付流程——充值、提现、转账——每一个交易边界都做法币↔USDT 转换。","Three wallet protocols — OMNI · ERC-20 · TRC-20 — exact-decimal balance handling, config-driven currency paths.":"三种钱包协议——OMNI · ERC-20 · TRC-20——余额用精确小数处理,币种路径由配置驱动。","Two years in production across three wallet protocols; later currencies reused the same config-driven paths instead of re-opening them.":"横跨三种钱包协议、两年生产运行;后来的币种复用同一套配置驱动的路径,而不是重新打开它们。","The platform needed cryptocurrency deposits and withdrawals alongside fiat. That is not one feature — it is a conversion concern at every transaction boundary: every deposit, withdrawal and transfer now has two currencies on either side of it, and the amounts have to agree exactly.":"平台需要在法币之外支持加密货币的充值与提现。这不是一个功能——而是每一个交易边界上的转换问题:每一笔充值、提现、转账的两侧从此各有一种货币,而金额必须严丝合缝地对上。","Two things made it hard. First, provider heterogeneity: some third-party providers could not hold crypto at all, so a USDT balance had to become fiat before it could touch them — and become USDT again on the way back. Second, precision: at a wallet edge, a rounding error is not a display bug, it is a real discrepancy against a real balance.":"难点有两个。第一,provider 的异构:有些第三方 provider 根本持有不了加密货币,所以 USDT 余额要先变成法币才能碰它们——回程再变回 USDT。第二,精度:在钱包边缘,一个舍入误差不是显示 bug,而是对着真实余额的一笔真实差异。","Financial correctness — a conversion at any boundary must reconcile exactly; there is no acceptable rounding drift on a balance.":"资金正确性——任何边界上的转换都必须精确对账;余额上不存在可接受的舍入漂移。","Provider heterogeneity — some providers could not hold USDT at all, and their limitations could not be allowed to leak into every call site.":"provider 异构——有些 provider 根本持有不了 USDT,而它们的局限不能被允许泄漏到每一个调用点。","On-chain reality — confirmations arrive more than once; a replayed notification must never credit twice.":"链上现实——确认会到达不止一次;重放的通知绝不能入账两次。","Three wallet protocols — OMNI, ERC-20 and TRC-20 each with their own transfer semantics, behind one platform-facing interface.":"三种钱包协议——OMNI、ERC-20、TRC-20 各有自己的转账语义,要收在一个面向平台的接口后面。","Longevity — a two-year epic, so the design had to absorb currencies added after us without re-opening the payment paths.":"长寿命——一个两年期的 epic,设计必须能吸收在我们之后新增的币种,而不用重新打开支付路径。","I drove the payments side for two years as half of a two-engineer pair, alongside the team's assistant lead. My part: the wallet protocol integrations (OMNI, ERC-20, TRC-20), USDT deposits and withdrawals, and threading fiat↔USDT conversion through every transaction boundary. The judgment call that shaped the module — absorbing provider differences in one cross-cutting compatibility layer instead of at every call site — was mine.":"支付这条线我推了两年,和团队的副手搭档、两个工程师负责。我的部分:钱包协议集成(OMNI、ERC-20、TRC-20)、USDT 的充值与提现,以及把法币↔USDT 转换织进每一个交易边界。塑造了这个模块的那个判断——把 provider 差异吸收进一个横切的兼容层,而不是散在每个调用点——是我做的。","USDT enters and leaves through the wallet protocols; everything in the middle is a boundary question. Each transaction boundary knows how to convert between fiat and USDT with exact-decimal math, and a single compatibility layer answers the question \"what currency does this provider actually settle in?\" — so a provider that can't hold USDT is handled in one place, invisibly to callers. Deposit crediting is a guarded state machine, so replayed on-chain confirmations are structurally a no-op.":"USDT 从钱包协议进、从钱包协议出;中间的一切都是边界问题。每个交易边界都知道如何用精确小数在法币和 USDT 之间转换,而一个统一的兼容层负责回答「这个 provider 实际用什么货币结算?」——所以持有不了 USDT 的 provider 只在一个地方被处理,对调用方不可见。充值入账是一台带守卫的状态机,重放的链上确认在结构上就是 no-op。","Transaction paths":"交易路径","Deposits: on-chain detection → confirmation → credit, each a guarded state transition. Withdrawals: platform balance out to a wallet address. Transfers: balance movement across providers — where conversion fires if the destination can't hold USDT.":"充值:链上侦测 → 确认 → 入账,每一步都是带守卫的状态迁移。提现:平台余额出金到一个钱包地址。转账:余额在 provider 之间移动——目的地持有不了 USDT 时,转换就在这里触发。","Walkthrough — one transfer":"走一遍——一笔转账","USDT-capable provider:":"能持有 USDT 的 provider:","the amount passes through unconverted.":"金额原样通过,不做转换。","Fiat-only provider:":"只支持法币的 provider:","the compatibility layer converts at the boundary — exact integer minor-unit math, no float anywhere near a balance — and converts back on the return leg.":"兼容层在边界处转换——精确的整数最小单位运算,余额附近没有任何浮点——回程再转换回来。","Replayed confirmation:":"重放的确认:","the credit state machine rejects the illegal transition; nothing is written twice.":"入账状态机拒绝这次非法迁移;没有任何东西被写第二次。","fiat↔USDT conversion at the boundary":"法币↔USDT 在边界处转换","wallet · USDT":"钱包 · USDT","compat layer":"兼容层","provider · USDT":"provider · USDT","provider · fiat":"provider · 法币","can't hold USDT? convert here — exact-decimal, one place":"持有不了 USDT?在这里转换——精确小数,只此一处","replayed confirmation ⟲ illegal transition — no second credit":"重放的确认 ⟲ 非法迁移——不会入账第二次","One compatibility layer, not per-call-site handling":"一个兼容层,而不是每个调用点各自处理","Let each payment flow check whether its provider can hold USDT and convert locally, or absorb the difference in one cross-cutting layer.":"让每条支付流程自己检查 provider 能不能持有 USDT、就地转换,还是把差异吸收进一个横切层。","One layer. Every call site asks \"what currency does this provider settle in?\" and gets a converted-or-passthrough answer.":"一个层。每个调用点只问「这个 provider 用什么货币结算?」,拿到的答案要么已转换、要么原样通过。","Provider heterogeneity was the recurring hazard; leaked into every call site, it would have been reimplemented — and mis-implemented — dozens of times.":"provider 异构是反复出现的隐患;一旦泄漏进每个调用点,它就会被重复实现——以及实现错——几十次。","The layer is on every payment path, so it carries concentrated blast radius and had to stay small and heavily reviewed.":"这一层压在每一条支付路径上,爆炸半径高度集中,所以必须保持小巧、接受高强度 review。","Exact-decimal math at the wallet edges":"钱包边缘的精确小数运算","Exact integer minor units at every conversion — no float ever touches a balance.":"每次转换都用精确的整数最小单位——浮点永远碰不到余额。","At a wallet edge a rounding error becomes a real discrepancy against a real balance. Reconciliation only works if both sides of a conversion are exact by construction.":"在钱包边缘,一个舍入误差会变成对着真实余额的真实差异。只有转换两侧由构造保证精确,对账才成立。","Rates are carried as ratios and conversion code is stricter to write; every boundary pays a small verbosity tax for exactness.":"汇率以比值形式携带,转换代码写起来更严格;每个边界都要为「精确」付一小笔啰嗦税。","Credit as a guarded state transition":"入账是一次带守卫的状态迁移","Deduplicate replayed on-chain confirmations with a processed-set check, or make crediting a state machine where a replay is an illegal transition.":"用「已处理集合」检查来给重放的链上确认去重,还是把入账做成状态机,让重放本身就是一次非法迁移。","State machine: detected → confirmed → credited, terminal at credited. A second \"confirmed\" changes nothing; an illegal jump throws.":"状态机:detected → confirmed → credited,credited 即终态。第二次「confirmed」什么都改变不了;非法跳转直接抛错。","On-chain confirmations arrive more than once by nature. A bolted-on check can be forgotten on a new path; a guarded transition cannot.":"链上确认天生就会到达不止一次。事后补上的检查会在新路径上被遗忘;带守卫的迁移不会。","Every new deposit variant has to be expressed as states and transitions first, which is slower to prototype than an ad-hoc handler.":"每一种新的充值变体都得先表达成状态和迁移,比随手写个 handler 的原型速度慢。","On a payment path, the failure modes are known in advance — the design's job is to make each one structurally harmless.":"在支付路径上,失败模式是可以预先知道的——设计的职责,是把每一种都变得在结构上无害。","The confirmation that arrives twice":"到达两次的确认","On-chain confirmations are delivered more than once — that's the transport's nature, not an edge case. Crediting is therefore a state transition guarded by the current state: detected → confirmed → credited, and credited is terminal. A replayed notification attempts an illegal transition and is rejected before it can write; the balance moves exactly once no matter how many times the network repeats itself.":"链上确认就是会被投递不止一次——这是传输层的天性,不是边缘情况。所以入账是一次由当前状态守卫的状态迁移:detected → confirmed → credited,credited 是终态。重放的通知会尝试一次非法迁移,在写入之前就被拒绝;不管网络重复多少遍,余额恰好只动一次。","The cent that goes missing at a boundary":"在边界上消失的那一分钱","Every fiat↔USDT conversion is a place where two ledgers must agree. Floating-point math would let them drift apart silently and surface weeks later as an unreconcilable difference. Conversion runs in exact integer minor units with rates as ratios — so when the two sides are compared, they match by construction, and a mismatch means a real problem, not arithmetic noise.":"每一次法币↔USDT 转换,都是两本账必须对上的地方。浮点运算会让它们悄悄漂离,几周后浮出水面时已是一笔无法对平的差异。转换用精确的整数最小单位、汇率以比值携带——所以两侧比对时,由构造保证相符;一旦对不上,那就是真问题,不是算术噪声。","The provider that can't hold USDT":"持有不了 USDT 的 provider","Some third-party providers couldn't hold crypto at all. Handled naively, every flow touching such a provider would need its own conversion logic — and each copy is a chance to get it wrong. Instead the difference is absorbed once, in the compatibility layer: callers move value; the layer decides whether that value crosses the boundary as USDT or as converted fiat, and converts back on the return leg.":"有些第三方 provider 根本持有不了加密货币。如果处理得天真,每条碰到这种 provider 的流程都得有自己的转换逻辑——而每份拷贝都是一次做错的机会。实际做法是把差异吸收一次,放在兼容层里:调用方只管移动价值;这一层决定价值以 USDT 还是以转换后的法币跨过边界,回程再转换回来。","The currency added after us":"在我们之后加进来的币种","The rails were built over two years, but currencies keep arriving after the epic closes. Because the payment paths are config-driven — currency behaviour is data, not branching code — later currencies were added by configuration rather than by re-opening deposit, withdrawal and transfer logic that had already earned its production trust.":"这套通道花了两年建成,但 epic 收尾之后,新币种还在不断到来。因为支付路径是配置驱动的——币种行为是数据,不是分支代码——后来的币种靠配置就能加上,而不用重新打开那些早已挣得生产信任的充值、提现、转账逻辑。","Same discipline as the rest of the platform: Jest for the units that matter — the state machine's transition table and the exact-decimal conversion math — and integration tests against real dependencies via Testcontainers rather than mocks. Payment paths sit inside the weekly regression run, so every release re-exercises deposits, withdrawals and transfers, including the replayed-confirmation case: fire the same confirmation twice, assert the balance moved once.":"和平台其他部分同一套纪律:要紧的单元用 Jest 测——状态机的迁移表和精确小数的转换运算——集成测试通过 Testcontainers 对着真实依赖跑,而不是 mock。支付路径都在每周回归里,所以每次发版都会重新走一遍充值、提现、转账,包括重放确认这个用例:同一个确认发两次,断言余额只动了一次。","The compatibility layer sits on every payment path — one place to fix provider differences, but also one place whose defects touch everything, so it moves slower than the code around it.":"兼容层压在每一条支付路径上——修 provider 差异只需一处,但缺陷也会从这一处波及一切,所以它的演进比周围的代码更慢。","Exact integer minor-unit arithmetic makes every conversion more verbose than a float multiply; that tax is paid at every boundary, deliberately.":"精确的整数最小单位运算,让每次转换都比一次浮点乘法啰嗦;这笔税在每个边界都要交,而且是有意为之。","Expressing crediting as a state machine means new deposit variants are slower to prototype — states and transitions first, behaviour second.":"把入账表达成状态机,意味着新的充值变体原型更慢——先有状态和迁移,再谈行为。","Two engineers over two years is a long, narrow investment; the payoff only shows when later currencies ride the same rails for free.":"两个工程师、两年时间,是一笔又长又窄的投资;回报要等到后来的币种免费搭上同一套轨道时才显现。","Crypto rails live across every payment flow — deposits, withdrawals and transfers.":"加密货币通道活在每一条支付流程里——充值、提现、转账。","Two years in production across three wallet protocols: OMNI, ERC-20, TRC-20.":"横跨三种钱包协议、两年生产运行:OMNI、ERC-20、TRC-20。","Replayed on-chain confirmations are structurally harmless — credit happens exactly once, guarded by state.":"重放的链上确认在结构上无害——入账恰好一次,由状态守卫。","Conversions reconcile exactly — no float ever touches a balance at a wallet edge.":"转换精确对账——在钱包边缘,浮点永远碰不到余额。","Later currencies reused the same config-driven paths instead of re-opening them.":"后来的币种复用同一套配置驱动的路径,而不是重新打开它们。","Provider heterogeneity is where payment integrations rot: the moment one call site starts special-casing a provider, every call site eventually will. Absorbing the difference in one layer was the single decision this module's longevity rests on. And precision is not a detail to handle later — at a wallet edge, exactness has to be a property of the arithmetic itself, because a rounding error there isn't a bug report, it's a discrepancy against a real balance that someone has to reconcile by hand.":"provider 异构是支付集成开始腐烂的地方:一旦有一个调用点开始给某个 provider 开特例,每个调用点迟早都会。把差异吸收进一个层,是这个模块的长寿所依赖的那一个决定。而精度不是可以以后再处理的细节——在钱包边缘,精确必须是运算本身的属性,因为那里的舍入误差不是一张 bug 单,而是一笔对着真实余额的差异,得有人手工去对平。","Next: Cross-Stack Rewards Pipeline →":"下一篇:跨栈发奖 pipeline →","case 08 / 08":"案例 08 / 08","Cross-Stack Rewards":"跨栈发奖","Four services, three languages, a reward path where a double-pay is real loss — the layer that makes payout happen exactly once, with zero legacy changes.":"4 个服务、3 种语言、一条重复发放就是真实损失的发奖路径——让发放恰好一次的那层,旧系统 0 改动。","Designed the exactly-once reliability layer — the owned ledger and idempotency key. The service decomposition follows the platform's existing seams and wasn't mine to claim.":"设计了 exactly-once 可靠性层——自己 own 的台账和幂等 key。服务切分沿着平台现有的缝走,不是我可以邀功的。","Four services in three languages; real-time detection on the event stream; one durable 7-day workflow per enrolled user.":"三种语言的四个服务;在事件流上做实时侦测;每个报名用户一条为期 7 天的持久 workflow。","Java/Flink stream job · Rust + Temporal workflow engine · NestJS reward facade · atomic claims ledger.":"Java/Flink 流式作业 · Rust + Temporal workflow 引擎 · NestJS 发奖 facade · 原子的 claims 台账。","Exactly-once under both workflow replays and message redeliveries; zero changes to legacy services; verified end-to-end in pre-production.":"在 workflow replay 和消息重投两种情况下都 exactly-once;旧系统服务 0 改动;在 pre-production 完成端到端验证。","Marketing wanted automatic, time-boxed missions for users close to their next loyalty tier: detect them in real time, run a 7-day window, and grant the tier upgrade instantly on success. That grant sits on a financially sensitive path — a duplicate payout is a real loss, not a cosmetic bug.":"市场团队想要自动化、限时的任务,面向接近下一忠诚度等级的用户:实时侦测他们,跑一个 7 天窗口,成功后立刻发放等级升级。这个发放坐在一条资金敏感路径上——重复发放是真实损失,不是外观 bug。","The hard part is that duplicates arrive from two independent sources. The event stream delivers at-least-once, and the workflow engine replays histories on recovery — so the grant step can legitimately run twice even when every component is behaving correctly. The pipeline also spans four services in three languages, and the legacy reward systems it ends in could not be modified.":"难点在于重复来自两个独立的来源。事件流是 at-least-once 投递,workflow 引擎恢复时会重放历史——所以即使每个组件都表现正确,发放这一步也可能名正言顺地跑两次。这条 pipeline 还横跨三种语言的四个服务,而它最终落地的 legacy 发奖系统不允许修改。","Financial correctness — a duplicate grant is a real loss; the payout must happen exactly once per user, tier, and month.":"资金正确性——重复发放就是真实损失;每个用户、等级、月份,发放必须恰好一次。","Two independent duplicate sources — at-least-once delivery from the stream and history replay from the workflow engine — both had to be neutralized by the same design.":"两个独立的重复来源——事件流的 at-least-once 投递和 workflow 引擎的历史重放——必须被同一个设计同时化解。","Zero changes to legacy services — the grant had to go through the existing upgrade path untouched.":"旧系统服务 0 改动——发放必须原封不动地走现有升级路径。","Cross-stack composition — four services in three languages, so the correctness guarantee could not rely on any one runtime's features.":"跨栈组合——三种语言的四个服务,所以正确性保证不能依赖任何单一运行时的特性。","Config consistency — mission thresholds used by more than one service could never be allowed to disagree.":"配置一致性——被多个服务使用的任务阈值,永远不允许出现分歧。","My design is the reliability layer on top of the pipeline: the atomic claims ledger that gates enrollment, the human-readable idempotency key that gates the grant, and the single-owner rule for thresholds. I built the chain end-to-end across the four services, composing the platform's proven engines rather than building new ones, and I put the rollout through a dry-run-by-default plan and an outside red-team before calling it safe. The decomposition into detect / orchestrate / grant follows boundaries the platform already had — I claim the layer that makes it correct, not the seams.":"我设计的是 pipeline 之上的那层可靠性:把住报名的原子 claims 台账、把住发放的人类可读幂等 key,以及阈值的单一 owner 规则。这条链我端到端做穿了四个服务,组合平台已被验证的引擎,而不是造新的;上线走的是 dry-run 默认开的方案,还请了外部 red-team 过一遍才说它安全。发现 / 编排 / 发放的切分沿的是平台本来就有的边界——我认领的是让它正确的那一层,不是那些缝。","Three stages on existing platform seams: a Java/Flink job filters the event stream and computes entry-anchored goals from a lookup table; a Rust + Temporal engine runs one durable workflow per user for the 7-day window; a NestJS facade grants the upgrade through the existing legacy path. Exactly-once is layered on top — an atomic claims ledger (one chance per user, tier, month) gates enrollment, and a human-readable idempotency key gates the grant.":"三个阶段落在平台现有的缝上:一个 Java/Flink 作业过滤事件流,按查表计算以进入时刻为锚点的目标;一个 Rust + Temporal 引擎给每个用户跑一条覆盖 7 天窗口的持久 workflow;一个 NestJS facade 通过现有 legacy 路径发放升级。exactly-once 分层叠在上面——一张原子的 claims 台账(每个用户、等级、月份只有一次机会)把住报名,一个人类可读的幂等 key 把住发放。","Detect → orchestrate → grant":"发现 → 编排 → 发放","Each stage reuses an engine the platform already runs: the streaming platform for detection, the workflow engine for the time-boxed window, the reward facade for the grant. Nothing new was built where something proven existed.":"每个阶段都复用平台已经在跑的引擎:侦测交给流处理平台,限时窗口交给 workflow 引擎,发放交给发奖 facade。凡是有现成、已验证的东西,就不造新的。","Walkthrough — how a duplicate dies":"走一遍——一个重复是怎么死掉的","the ledger accepts exactly one claim per user, tier, and month — a redelivered detection event collides and stops.":"台账对每个用户、等级、月份恰好只接受一次 claim——被重投的侦测事件撞上就停。","the key":"这个 key","is inserted before the payout; a workflow replay finds the key already present and returns without paying.":"在发放之前先插入;workflow replay 发现 key 已经存在,不发放就返回。","Either way:":"无论哪种:","the user is upgraded once, and the key is readable at a glance when someone has to debug it.":"用户只被升级一次,而当有人要排查时,这个 key 一眼就能读懂。","Flink · Java":"Flink · Java","Rust · Temporal":"Rust · Temporal","Compose existing engines, not build new ones":"组合现有引擎,而不是造新的","Build a bespoke mission service owning detection, timing and payout — or place each stage on an engine the platform already runs.":"造一个把侦测、计时、发放都揽下的专用任务服务,还是把每个阶段放到平台已经在跑的引擎上。","Boundaries follow existing seams: the streaming platform detects, the workflow engine holds the 7-day window, the reward facade grants.":"边界沿着现有的缝走:流处理平台负责侦测,workflow 引擎握着 7 天窗口,发奖 facade 负责发放。","Every engine in the chain was already proven in this platform; the only genuinely new problem was making the composition exactly-once.":"链条里的每个引擎都已在这个平台上得到验证;唯一真正新的问题,是让这个组合做到 exactly-once。","Four services in three languages means no single runtime can carry the correctness guarantee — it had to live in shared data, not in any one framework's features.":"三种语言的四个服务,意味着没有任何单一运行时能承载正确性保证——它只能活在共享的数据里,而不是某个框架的特性里。","Layered exactly-once with a human-readable key":"分层的 exactly-once,配一个人类可读的 key","One dedupe check at the payout, an opaque hash key, or two independent gates — ledger at enrollment, idempotency key at the grant.":"在发放处做一次去重检查、用一个不透明的哈希 key,还是设两道独立的门——报名处是台账,发放处是幂等 key。","Both gates, and the key is readable:":"两道门都要,而且 key 是可读的:","Duplicates come from two independent sources — message redelivery and workflow replay — so a single gate leaves one source uncovered. A readable key means an on-call engineer can see at a glance who was granted what, and why a second attempt was refused.":"重复来自两个独立来源——消息重投和 workflow replay——只设一道门就总有一个来源没被盖住。可读的 key 意味着值班工程师一眼就能看出谁被发了什么,以及第二次尝试为什么被拒。","Two writes on the happy path instead of one, and the key format becomes a contract — changing it later would invalidate the dedupe history.":"happy path 上从一次写变成两次写,而且 key 的格式成了契约——以后一改,去重历史就作废。","Zero legacy changes — grant through the existing path":"旧系统 0 改动——通过现有路径发放","Modify the legacy reward systems to understand missions, or wrap the existing upgrade path behind a thin facade and leave legacy untouched.":"改造 legacy 发奖系统让它认识「任务」,还是用一个薄 facade 包住现有升级路径,legacy 原封不动。","A NestJS facade calls the existing upgrade path as-is; the mission concept never leaks into legacy code.":"一个 NestJS facade 原样调用现有升级路径;「任务」这个概念永远不会泄漏进 legacy 代码。","The legacy path already carries the platform's real upgrades — reusing it means the grant behaves identically to every other upgrade, with no new code on the sensitive side.":"legacy 路径承载着平台真实的升级——复用它,意味着这次发放和其他每一次升级行为完全一致,敏感一侧没有任何新代码。","The pipeline inherits the legacy path's behavior and limits wholesale; anything it can't express, the mission can't grant.":"pipeline 把 legacy 路径的行为和限制整个继承下来;它表达不了的东西,任务就发放不了。","The failure modes this layer was designed against — each one is structural to the platform, not hypothetical.":"这一层就是针对这些失败模式设计的——每一种都是平台结构性的,不是假想的。","The message that arrives twice":"到达两次的消息","The event stream is at-least-once by contract: the same detection event can be redelivered after a consumer restart or a rebalance. Without a gate, a redelivered event enrolls the same user twice and the mission pays twice. The ledger makes enrollment an atomic insert — one chance per user, tier, and month — so the second delivery collides on the claim and stops. Recovery is nothing: the duplicate simply dies at the door.":"事件流按契约就是 at-least-once:同一个侦测事件在消费者重启或 rebalance 之后会被重投。没有门,重投的事件就会给同一个用户报名两次,任务就发两次。台账把报名做成一次原子插入——每个用户、等级、月份只有一次机会——所以第二次投递会在 claim 上撞车、停下。恢复什么都不用做:重复就死在门口。","The workflow that runs its history again":"把自己历史重跑一遍的 workflow","The workflow engine recovers by replaying history on another worker — which means the grant step can execute again even though the first attempt succeeded. The idempotency key is inserted before the payout: a replay finds":"workflow 引擎的恢复方式,是在另一个 worker 上重放历史——这意味着即使第一次已经成功,发放这一步也可能再执行一次。幂等 key 在发放之前先插入:replay 会发现","already present and returns without paying. The two gates are independent on purpose — either source of duplicates is stopped even if the other gate were bypassed.":"已经存在,于是不发放就返回。两道门刻意相互独立——哪怕其中一道被绕过,另一个来源的重复也照样被拦住。","Two repos, two versions of the same number":"两个仓库,同一个数字的两个版本","Mission thresholds are consumed by more than one service. If each repository carried its own copy, a config edit in one place would silently split the pipeline's view of the goal. So every threshold has exactly one owner — a lookup table — and producers broadcast unconditionally; consumers never hold a local copy that can drift. Two repositories can never disagree about the same number, because only one of them has it.":"任务阈值被多个服务消费。如果每个仓库都留一份自己的拷贝,某处的一次配置修改就会悄悄撕裂 pipeline 对目标的认知。所以每个阈值恰好只有一个 owner——一张查询表——生产者无条件广播;消费者从不持有可能漂移的本地拷贝。两个仓库永远不可能对同一个数字有分歧,因为它只在其中一个手里。","The goal that changes mid-mission":"任务进行到一半会变的目标","A 7-day window outlives config edits. If a threshold is raised on day three, users already running would see their goal move under them. Goals are entry-anchored: computed once at enrollment from the lookup table and fixed for the life of the workflow — later edits apply to new enrollments only. A running mission always finishes under the rules it started with.":"一个 7 天窗口活得比配置修改更久。如果第三天调高了阈值,已经在跑的用户会眼看目标从脚下移走。目标以进入时刻为锚:报名时按查询表算一次,workflow 存续期内固定不变——之后的修改只作用于新的报名。进行中的任务,永远按它开始时的规则跑完。","The pipeline follows the platform's standard test discipline — Jest with integration tests against real dependencies via Testcontainers, and every path covered by the weekly regression suite. The tests that matter most here mirror the two duplicate sources: deliver the same detection event twice and assert one enrollment; drive the grant step through a replay and assert one payout.":"pipeline 遵循平台标准的测试纪律——Jest 加上通过 Testcontainers 对真实依赖跑的集成测试,每条路径都在每周回归套件里。这里最要紧的测试正对应两个重复来源:同一个侦测事件投两次,断言只报名一次;让发放这一步经历一次 replay,断言只发放一次。","Beyond tests, the chain was verified end-to-end against production-like traffic in the pre-production lane, with funnel metrics at every stage — detected, enrolled, completed, granted — so a lost or doubled record is visible as a stage-to-stage mismatch. The rollout itself was dry-run by default, and I put the plan through an outside red-team before calling it safe.":"测试之外,这条链在 pre-production 通道里对着接近生产的流量做了端到端验证,每一级都有漏斗指标——侦测、报名、完成、发放——所以一条丢失或翻倍的记录,会以级与级不匹配的形式显形。上线本身是 dry-run 默认开,方案还请外部 red-team 过了一遍,我才说它安全。","Layered exactly-once costs an extra write and an extra collection on the hot path — accepted, because either duplicate source alone can produce a real loss.":"分层的 exactly-once 在热路径上多付一次写、多一个 collection——接受,因为任何一个重复来源单独就能造成真实损失。","The human-readable key is a contract: its format can't change without invalidating the dedupe history, so it's deliberately boring and minimal.":"人类可读的 key 是一份契约:格式一改,去重历史就作废,所以它被刻意做得无聊而极简。","Granting through the untouched legacy path means inheriting its behavior and limits wholesale — the price of zero legacy changes.":"通过原封不动的 legacy 路径发放,意味着把它的行为和限制整个继承下来——这是旧系统 0 改动的代价。","Three languages across four services keeps each stage on its best engine, but every cross-service guarantee has to live in data, and debugging spans three toolchains.":"四个服务用三种语言,让每个阶段都跑在最合适的引擎上,但每一条跨服务的保证都只能活在数据里,排查也要横跨三套工具链。","Exactly-once payout under both workflow replays and message redeliveries — the two duplicate sources are gated independently.":"在 workflow replay 和消息重投两种情况下发放都 exactly-once——两个重复来源各有独立的门。","Zero changes to legacy services; the grant reuses the existing upgrade path as-is.":"旧系统服务 0 改动;发放原样复用现有升级路径。","Verified end-to-end against production-like traffic in the pre-production lane (QAT) — honest scope: pre-production, not production.":"在 pre-production 通道(QAT)对着接近生产的流量完成端到端验证——范围诚实:是预发布,不是生产。","Funnel metrics at every stage and a dry-run-by-default rollout, red-teamed before being called safe.":"每一级都有漏斗指标,上线 dry-run 默认开,经过 red-team 之后才说它安全。","The layer — owned ledger, readable key, detect / orchestrate / grant with single-owner config — is the template for the next mission types.":"这一层——自己 own 的台账、可读的 key、发现 / 编排 / 发放加配置单一 owner——是下一批任务类型的模板。","When a pipeline crosses runtimes, correctness can't be borrowed from any one framework — it has to live in data both sides can see, which is why the ledger and the key carry the guarantee instead of any engine feature. Duplicates from independent sources need independent gates; one check that \"should\" cover both is one bug away from covering neither. And observability is part of the design, not an add-on: a key a human can read and a funnel a human can diff are what make an exactly-once claim checkable rather than taken on faith.":"当 pipeline 横跨多个运行时,正确性没法向任何一个框架借——它必须活在两边都看得见的数据里,这就是为什么承载保证的是台账和 key,而不是某个引擎特性。来自独立来源的重复需要独立的门;一个「应该」两边都盖住的检查,离两边都盖不住只差一个 bug。而可观测性是设计的一部分,不是附加项:一个人能读懂的 key、一条人能 diff 的漏斗,才让 exactly-once 这个说法可以被验证,而不是靠信。","Next: Transaction Backbone →":"下一篇:交易主干 →","Problem":"问题","Problem:":"问题:","Constraints":"约束","Architecture":"架构","Options":"选项","Decision":"决定","Reason":"理由","Trade-off":"代价","Trade-offs":"取舍","Role":"角色","Scale":"规模","Stack":"技术栈","Outcome:":"结果:","Lifecycle":"生命周期","Selected":"精选","Transaction":"交易","Backbone":"主干","Support":"客服","System":"系统","Reporting":"报表","Engine":"引擎","processing":"处理着","Millions/day":"每天数百万","Arrival:":"到达:","Normalize:":"归一化:","Store:":"落库:","Reconcile:":"对账:","Seed:":"起点:","Rollback:":"回退:","Retry:":"重试:","Enrollment:":"登记:","Grant:":"发放:","background":"背景","you":"你","Résumé":"简历","Flow":"流程","Floating-point with careful rounding, a decimal library everywhere, or exact integer minor-unit arithmetic at the boundaries where value changes representation.":"小心舍入的浮点、到处用 decimal 库,还是在钱改变表示形式的边界上用精确的整数最小单位运算。"};
